title: broccoli salad
directions: Use flowerettes and small stems of broccoli. Fry and crumble bacon. Mix with cheese, onion and broccoli.

title: mexican layered taco dip
directions: Spread bean dip on a 14-inch round tray.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Put that on top
of bean dip. Dice tomatoes, green onions (stems included) and black olives. Grate Cheddar cheese.
Layer tomatoes, green onions and black olives in order and top with cheese.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: no boiling lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella, Parmesan and eggs.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread 1 cup sauce; layer 4 uncooked noodles, 1 cup sauce and 1/2 of Ricotta mixture.
Repeat; top with remaining 4 uncooked lasagne noodles and 2 cups sauce.
Reserve remaining sauce.
Cover with foil; bake 1 hour.
Remove foil; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve with remaining sauce, heated.

title: easy chinese chicken salad
directions: Cut lettuce and cucumber into bite-sized pieces.
Cut green onions into 1/2-inch pieces (separate green tops from white bottoms).
Cut Chinese parsley into 1/2-inch pieces (separate leaves from stems).
Completely cover chicken in pot with water. Add in white bottoms of green onions, stems of parsley and dash of salt.
Boil for 1/2 hour.
Remove chicken to cool.
Strain liquid to have clear chicken stock.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces. Put lettuce, cucumber, green onions, parsley, peanuts and chicken into large container.
Add Oriental dressing and toss completely so dressing is well spread.
Add won ton chips to top.
Serve.

title: tomato bean combo
directions: Drain beans.
Peel and cut up tomatoes.
Mix up all and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
It's juicy and delicious.

title: irish soda bread(low cholesterol)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Add raisins. Combine egg whites, buttermilk and oil.
Add to dry mixture.
Pour batter into a greased round iron frying pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat well all the ingredients except the oatmeal.
When they are smooth, mix in the oatmeal.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken casserole(serving size: 12)
directions: Drain broccoli and add rest of ingredients, except French fried onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, that has been greased.
Place in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
About 10 minutes before done, sprinkle onion on top. Continue cooking until brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add softened cream cheese and mix until well blended.
Stir in green chiles, then corn; mix well.
Bake in a casserole dish for 30 minutes.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, butter and pecans to crumble stage and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Stir once or twice during baking.
Beat egg whites to make stiff peaks.
Add sugar, lemon juice and strawberries (place berries in blender before adding to egg whites).
Beat all at high speed.
Whip cream and fold in.
Pour over crumb mixture and freeze.
Cut in squares to serve and garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: ambrosia cookie pie
directions: Cream cheese with sugar and pineapple liquid.
Mix until smooth.
Beat cream until stiff.
Fold into cream cheese mixture. Fold in drained pineapple, Mandarin oranges and coconut.
Pour in baked crust or graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Use a large container for marinade.
Beat eggs well.
Add other ingredients.
If you can, use fresh black pepper, onion and garlic.
Mix well.
Add chicken and marinate at least 24 hours in the refrigerator.
Line 2 shallow roasting pans with foil.
Place chicken on pans in single layers.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° until crisp.
Turn every 15 minutes and baste with marinade.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients together.
Cook until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Add vanilla; cool.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan and when nearly cold, cut into squares.

title: shrimp tetrazzini
directions: Melt 1/4 cup oleo in pan; add onions and cook until tender. Mix in flour and gradually blend in next 4 ingredients.
Cook, stirring for 3 minutes.
After sauce begins to simmer, stir in 1/4 cup cheese; set aside.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Melt butter
in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and cook over low
heat,
stirring constantly.
Add milk and bring to a boil. Remove
from
heat,
add
vanilla
and let cool to room temperature.
Then beat in sugar and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Chill until firm.
Keep refrigerated.

title: calico baked beans
directions: In large skillet, brown beef and onion in butter; drain well. Place in large casserole with bacon. In medium bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses, chili powder, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add kidney, white, black and pork and beans to casserole. Pour sugar mixture on top; blend well.

title: southern dish casserole
directions: In a greased casserole layer onions and potatoes and add salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 can corn, 1/2 can peas, then repeat layers, starting with onions and potatoes.
Place pork sausage on top and then pour tomato soup over all.

title: mexican scrambled eggs
directions: Place butter in microproof dish or pie plate and cook on High for about 1 minute.
Swirl butter to coat bottom.
Add chiles, tomato and onion and cook on High for 2 minutes.
Beat eggs, milk, garlic powder, salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Pour over tomato mixture.
Cook (microwave) on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until eggs are barely set, stirring outer edge of egg to center several times. Sprinkle with cheese.
Continue to cook (microwave) on High for 1 to 2 minutes until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: graham cracker crunchies
directions: Put 1 layer graham crackers in flat pan.
(Break in 4 pieces and place very close together.)
Bring butter, margarine and sugar to rolling boil; boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let set for just a second to let syrup soak in, but not too long, or they will stick and you will never get them out of pan.
Cool on rack.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together soup and cream cheese.
Add remainder of ingredients.

title: italian meat pie
directions: Cook beef and bell pepper in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink; drain. Stir in water, tomato paste and sauce mix. Cover; reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes. Sprinkle half of Parmesan cheese on bottom of frozen pastry shell; top with half of meat mixture and sprinkle with 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese. Top with remaining meat mixture and Parmesan cheese. Place shell on baking sheet. Bake on lowest oven rack at 400° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese; bake 5 more minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken noodle soup with vegetables
directions: Cook chicken or boil until done.
Cool and pull meat from bones.
Place in crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients except for egg noodles.
Cook in crock-pot on high for approximately 8 to 10 hours.
Approximately 20 minutes before serving, add egg noodles. Cook until noodles are done.

title: judy's squash pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine with squash.
Add condensed milk and beat well with electric mixer.
Add pumpkin pie spice.
Divide mixture equally between 2 unbaked deep-dish pie shells.
Cover edges of pie shell with foil.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for about 45 minutes or until done and lightly brown.

title: 20 minute tamale pie
directions: Brown beef; add onion.
Drain excess fat.
Mix rest of ingredients, except cheese. Reduce heat, sprinkle cheese on top, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve hot with salsa.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Makes a skillet full.

title: chinese chicken slaw
directions: Break up noodles and add to remaining.
Set aside.
Use seasoning pack from noodles and mix with one cup oil, 4 tablespoons vinegar and 4 tablespoons sugar; mix together.
Pour over all ingredients; toss and chill overnight or at least 2 hours.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Spread margarine on one side of bread slices; cut bread into small cubes.
Combine bread cubes, sausage, cheese, salt and pepper; stir well.
Beat eggs until foamy; stir in milk.
Add egg mixture to sausage mixture, stirring well.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: libby's corn casserole
directions: Saute peppers and onions in the hot oleo.
Mix corn bread mix, eggs and both corns.
Stir until all mix is moist.
Add the peppers and onions.
Pour into a greased oblong baking dish.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cover top with sour cream and grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine water and frozen concentrates.
Stir to dissolve. Stir in pineapple juice, sugar and lime juice; stir to dissolve sugar.
Chill.
To serve, pour half of the mixture of juices over ice in large punch bowl.
Slowly pour in 2 bottles of the ginger ale and 1 bottle of the carbonated water.
Stir gently to mix. Garnish with strawberries and orange slice, if desired.
Repeat with remaining ingredients when needed.
Makes 90 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: toad in the hole
directions: Mix flour, milk and egg together to form Yorkshire pudding batter.
Pour mixture in pan.
Roll out sausage mix.
Cut in strips and lay in pan in threes across the pan.
Cooking time is 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with mashed or baked potatoes and vegetable.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Fold in well drained crushed pineapple and coconut.
Spread over cake mix and sprinkle with nutmeats.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sour cream and stir until dissolved.
Place in refrigerator and chill until mixture gets to thickness of egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in mold and refrigerate until congealed.
Will make a large Pyrex oblong container full.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Brown roast rolled in flour.
Cook all day in slow cooker or crock-pot.
After 4 hours, slice and put back in juice and continue cooking.
Great for a quick hot beef sandwich.
Freezes well for individual servings.

title: pecan pie i
directions: Add all ingredients in order and mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Filling should appear slightly less set at center than at outer edge.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; blend in flour.
Cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and milk, alternately.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon this in 2-quart casserole and top with flaky pastry.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Saute eggplant and onion in large skillet until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, cottage cheese, tomatoes, marjoram and pepper. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: seafood sword kabobs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients for basting sauce. Peel and devein shrimp, leaving last section of shell and tail intact. Add shrimp and scallops to basting sauce and let stand 1 hour at room temperature, stirring to evenly coat the meat.

title: marvelous meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of spaghetti sauce, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg.
In 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Heat remaining sauce and place on meat loaf and serve.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut and peel eggs lengthwise into halves.
Slip out yolks; mash with a fork.
Mix in salt, mustard, pepper and mayonnaise. Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it lightly.
Arrange eggs on a large serving plate.
Cover and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.

title: filled oatmeal bars
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar and salt.
Blend in flour and oats until fine.
Press 3/4 of mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat condensed milk in saucepan.
Stir in chips and nuts. Pour over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or a light golden brown. Butterscotch chips may be substituted for the chocolate chips.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Saute onions with hamburger.
Add taco sauce, 1/2 can enchilada sauce and green chilies; let simmer. Grate cheese.
Put hamburger mixture, cheese (all but 1 cup) and onion inside each corn tortilla; roll up.
Put in 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce over tortillas; sprinkle remaining cheese.
Bake in oven at 425° until cheese melts.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Rinse turkey and pat dry.
Rub seasoning inside and out of turkey.
Wash you hands!!!

title: jacque's favorite pumpkin bars
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Place in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter. Add brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix this with dry ingredients and spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle top with package of chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(One minute after baking, take knife and cut through dough to marbelize chocolate chips.)
Cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In 2-3 quart casserole dish (or small roaster),
layer cooked rice and broccoli.
Mix soup and water, pour over chicken. Sprinkle salt and pepper and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake covered in 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend egg and 8 tablespoons sugar.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Alternately add flour and milk to egg mixture; beat well after each addition.
Stir in 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Fold in blueberries.
Turn batter into a greased 8-inch square baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until top springs back when lightly touched.
Brush top with remaining butter.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers and mix rest of ingredients.
Blend well.
Line cracker box with waxed paper.
Pack mixture in box.
Cover tightly.
Place in refrigerator for at least 2 weeks.

title: grandma's sweet bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: braised stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut pocket in each chop.
Set aside.
Saute the apple and onion in the margarine in a medium size skillet until soft, about 4 minutes.
Mix in the bread crumbs, raisins, salt, sage and pepper.
Spoon stuffing into chop pockets.
Close openings with toothpicks.
Dredge the chops in flour.
Brown the chops on both sides in oil.
Add the broth to the skillet.
Cover the skillet and cook over medium-low heat for about 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Remove picks.
Garnish with apple slices and parsley, if desired.

title: microwave chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in microwave-safe dish and pour mixture over top.
Let marinate a minimum of 2 hours, or let sit overnight.
Stir occasionally. Keep marinating chicken in fridge.
Microwave on High 8 minutes. Rearrange after 4 minutes.
Let stand for 2 minutes before serving.
Good over rice.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Brown meat and add spaghetti sauce and seasonings.
In a greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish, make layers in order:
noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese slices and sauce.
Repeat.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: wine cooler punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in punch bowl.
Top with sherbet.

title: indian corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar; beat well.
Add cheese and corn.
Stir in 3/4 of the bacon.
Pour mixture into ungreased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining bacon over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Boil broccoli and peas for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain well and cool.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: salsa
directions: Peel tomatoes; quarter. Mix with other vegetables and cook for 1 1/2 hours. Drain the juices. Add salt, sugar and vinegar. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours until thick. Fill jars and seal.

title: that chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake approximately 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and egg pie
directions: Boil ham to have broth.
Then dice ham.
Boil eggs and slice. Place 1 cup ham in a baking dish.
Add half of the sliced eggs. Sprinkle salt and pepper and cover with broth.
Make your dough; mix flour, oil and cold water to make dough, rolling it very thin. Place over ham, eggs and broth.
Brown good.
Repeat the ham, egg and dough layers.
Cover the dough good with butter so it will brown good.
If it seems dry, you can add some milk and water and let it come to a boil.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped into sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes a large amount.

title: church windows
directions: Melt together.
Remove from heat and let cool down until marshmallows won't melt. Then stir in 1 package miniature marshmallows.
Put in a buttered 9-inch square pan and refrigerate.

title: jack's favorite ribs
directions: In a 6-quart stockpot, boil 4 quarts of water. Add ribs. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes just until tender when pierced with a fork. Drain and as soon as you can handle them, peel and dice.

Toss with the lemon juice, oil and salt to taste (the flavor is better when they have this preliminary dressing while very warm and the potatoes, thus coated, won't absorb as much mayonnaise later). Cool.
Add the pepper, celery and chopped eggs.
Blend 1 cup mayonnaise with vinegar, then toss over the potato salad, gently folding until all pieces are coated.
If the potatoes seem a little dry, add more mayonnaise.
Line a bowl or a platter with lettuce leaves and pile the potato salad in the middle.

title: fast flounder fillets
directions: Place fish in 9 or 10-inch glass pie plate.
Pour milk over fillets. Dot with butter and season with remaining ingredients. Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: beef tips
directions: Cook all ingredients in crock-pot for about 5 to 6 hours. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: mini open faced gyros
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut pocket bread in 12 wedges; split each in half, forming 24 triangles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and flour together well. Add lemon juice slowly and mix well. Slowly add melted margarine and mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Mix mustard and jelly in a crock-pot on low heat.
(Use a wire whisk to blend these 2 ingredients together.)
Add Little Smokies and heat for an hour or so.
Serve hot.

title: apple and pecan squash(serves 4)
directions: Cut squash into halves crosswise; discard seeds.
Place, cut side down, in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Scoop out pulp, reserving shells.

title: stir-fry pork
directions: Mix pork with combined cornstarch, sherry, soy sauce and ginger; let stand 1/2 hour.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all together in iron skillet at 425° until brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Heat broth; add celery and onion which have been sauteed in margarine until transparent but not browned.
Add to broth; add corn and chicken pieces and heat until boiling.
Add rivvels; season with salt and pepper.

title: italian vinaigrette
directions: Put salt, peppers, mustard and sugar in jar with a screw top. Using a garlic press, add garlic.
Add oil and vinegar (according to taste) and shake vigorously.
Use at room temperature.
Extra may be refrigerated for a week.

title: sauerkraut dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or 15 to 20 minutes in microwave on High.
Serve warm with Fritos or taco chips.

title: squash puppies
directions: Combine corn meal and flour in mixing bowl. Add onion and squash. Stir in egg and enough milk to make a stiff batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat.
Fry until brown on all sides.
Drain and serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: make-day-ahead-salad
directions: Drain all of the ingredients well and marinate in the refrigerator overnight in the following mixture:

title: porcupines
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salt, celery salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture into small balls.
Place meatballs in oven baking dish.
Mix together tomato sauce, 1 cup water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 more minutes.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Layer cabbage, onion and green pepper in a large bowl; sprinkle sugar on top.
Do not stir.
Bring to a boil vinegar, salt, celery seed and dry mustard and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over slaw and do not stir.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Toss before serving.
This slaw can be kept in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks or you may freeze.

title: fruit salad
directions: Using canned fruit in its own juice, drain and combine in a large glass bowl.
Slice bananas into fruit; add coconut.
Stir to combine.

title: apple scallops
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Cut in butter. Add nuts.
Place apples in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover with flour mixture. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cherries.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with cherries on top.

title: oriental salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and put in large bowl.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and Tabasco together.
Bring to a boil. Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni by directions on box.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Layer macaroni and cheese in dish.
Top with milk.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican pate
directions: Mix the cream cheese and cottage cheese. Spread on dinner plate. Sprinkle 1/2 taco mix on top.
Layer vegetables.
Put Cheddar cheese and black olives on top.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms, bell pepper and zucchini until color brightens.
Season with salt and pepper and drain in colander. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook empty shells until they are lightly golden.
Line pie shells with Swiss cheese and then tomato slices. Fill with vegetables.

title: potato-spam casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; drain and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in small amount of oil.
Add can of condensed milk; simmer a few minutes.
Line casserole with pie crust; prick crust.
Add potatoes and cheese to onion, green pepper and milk sauce.
Place in pastry-lined casserole.
Cover with chopped Spam, then cover with top crust.
Cook about 1 hour at 350°.

title: paella #2
directions: *If threads are used, grind with mortar and pestle.

title: gail's chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt together in a large bowl.
Add water, oil, vanilla, vinegar and stir until smooth.
Do not overmix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not grease pan.

title: charleston tomato aspic
directions: Set Jell-O with
hot
water.
Mash or puree tomatoes in blender.
Add all other ingredients and chill in salad mold.

title: rice pudding casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: arnold's favorite log jams
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in large kettle.
Add noodles and nuts; mix and drop onto wax paper by tablespoons.
Cool.
Fast and easy.

title: pecan pie coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and beat again. Add margarine and beat. Add vanilla, then flour. Beat well. Add pecans and blend well. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Do not overbake. Should be a little gooey.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients.
Spread in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crumbs in 13 x 9-inch pan (glass dish works best).
Combine egg whites, sugar, thawed strawberries and lemon juice.
Beat with mixer on high to stiff peaks (about 10 minutes).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze about 6 hours.
Let stand 1/2 hour before serving.

title: rhubarb-pineapple jam
directions: Stir ingredients.
Let set 1/2 hour.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes. Stir well (watch carefully).
Add small package strawberry jello. Stir well to dissolve.
Put in jars at once.

title: shrimp and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until just tender. Drain.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, alternate 1 layer each of the cooked macaroni, shrimp and diced eggs.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Top with a few large shrimp (if desired).
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan over low heat; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually blend in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and smooth.
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Bake uncovered in preheated 425° oven for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: caper-mustard marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in small screw-top jar.
Shake to mix well.
Use at once or refrigerate up to 1 week.
Use to marinate poultry or fish 1 to 2 hours before grilling.
Brush any remaining marinade over poultry or fish while grilling.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix the first 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Place in large casserole dish and bake 30 minutes. While in the oven mix 1 cup cornflake crumbs, 1/2 stick butter (melted) and 1/2 cup brown sugar for topping.
After casserole has baked for 30 minutes, remove it from the oven and put topping on it.
Bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: mama gail's spinach jello(popeye's delight)
directions: Mix jello by package directions, but use 1 cup less cold water. Add well drained spinach and pineapple. If spinach and pineapple settle to bottom, stir again when partially set. Keep refrigerated.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumber.
In medium bowl, with fork, beat water, vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper until well blended. Add cucumber slices and toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate. Serve as a relish or salad.
Serves 4.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water and salt until thread spins. Beat egg whites; add vanilla slowly. Pour syrup over beaten whites. Beat until thick; add pecans.

title: chicken, vegetable and cheese tortellini soup
directions: This is a very easy soup which can be altered according to what you have on hand.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy, about 20 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg.
Add lemon flavor, 1 spoonful at a time, beating thoroughly after each spoon. Slowly add 7-Up.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on bag.
Add margarine to rice while still warm.
Add corn and soup to rice mixture.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Top with one cup grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: peach delight
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Make batter of sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour over butter in baking dish. Pour peaches into batter; do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: chicken ranch pizza
directions: Prepare fajita marinade according to package directions.
Cut up chicken and marinate for 15 minutes.
Cook bacon and drain grease.
Drain chicken, discard marinade.
Saute chicken, cook completely.
Spread ranch dressing over pizza crust.
Sprinkle 1 c. cheese over dressing.
Top with chicken and crumbled bacon. Sprinkle remaining
cheese on top.
Bake 10 - 15 minutes at 450.

title: charlene's egg noodles
directions: Mix eggs, shortening and salt.
Add small amounts of flour at a time until dough is very stiff.
Place on heavily floured board. Sprinkle flour over dough.
Roll out on board.
Sprinkle with flour again.
Roll up into a roll.
Circle.
Slice off in very thin strips and place in boiling chicken broth.
Take chicken off the bone and place in noodles.
Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes, being careful not to let the noodles stick.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan; cover with 2 slices bacon, if desired. Pour one 8 ounce can tomato sauce over the top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg with whisk; stir in milk and oil.
Blend dry ingredients and stir in until flour is moistened. Blend in blueberries.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: fancy french onion soup(serving size:  6)
directions: Separate onion slices into rings; saute sliced onion and garlic in butter over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes or until very tender and translucent.
Add flour, stirring until smooth. Gradually add beef broth and water.
Bring to a boil; cover. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in pepper and Madeira (optional).
Remove from heat.
Place 6 ovenproof serving bowls on a baking sheet.
Place 1 toasted bread slice in each bowl; ladle soup into bowls.
Sprinkle each serving evenly with Mozzarella cheeses; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil 6-inches from heat 1 minute or until cheese melts.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in fine crumbs.
Press 1/2 of the crumb mixture into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish and bake at 325° until brown.
Cover with 2 cups frozen raspberries.
Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk and pour over berries.
Cover with remaining crumb mix.
Bake until batter pulls away from sides at 325°.

title: chicken nuggets(appetizer)
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Heat 3-inches of oil in a large heavy saucepan over medium heat until it reaches 375°, adjust heat to maintain temperature.
Meanwhile beat egg and water in large bowl until well mixed.
Add flour, salt, and pepper, stirring to form smooth batter.
Dip chicken pieces into batter, draining off excess.
Fry chicken, a few pieces at a time, in hot oil about 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Serve with sauces.

title: almond roca
directions: *Keep the dust pieces that come off while chopping.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Coat chicken with a mixture of the flour to which you have added a teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Then brown chicken pieces in the hot shortening.
Remove chicken pieces to a 3-quart casserole.
Cook celery and onions in skillet until tender but not brown.
Drain off excess fat; stir in soup, pimento and 3/4 cup water.
Pour over chicken in casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° until tender.
This takes about one hour.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix egg, sugar	and
soft
butter.
Add
flour,
baking powder, salt and
milk.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour in greased 8-inch pan and top with 1/2 cup sweetened fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, pepper sauce and vinegar; dip chicken in mixture and place in baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1 package dry dressing mix.
Bake until brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Prepare other original dressing mix as instructed on package.
Serve with celery sticks and chicken.

title: smoked tuna ball
directions: Mix the ingredients together, except pecans.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add brown sugar Karo white syrup and salt.
Bring to boil.
Stir.
Boil 5 minutes; do not stir (at medium).
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popped corn. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
One popper = 16 cups, approximately 3/4 cup of popcorn.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Bake in oven at 375° for an hour and a half.

title: parmesan oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley (if using), garlic salt and pepper.
Set aside. Dip chicken pieces in salad dressing and dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Coat a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Place dredged chicken pieces in dish.
Bake for 45 minutes or until chicken tests done.
Juices will run clear when meat is pierced with a fork.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients and half the vinegar in a blender.
Blend well.
With blender still running, add oil and remaining vinegar.
Blend thoroughly.
This method prevents dressing from separating.
Stir in the celery seed.
Keeps indefinitely in the refrigerator.

title: saucy pork and peppers
directions: Squeeze juice from limes, reserving peel.
In a small bowl, combine lime juice, lime peel, soy sauce, oregano, thyme, cayenne pepper, garlic, parsley and Bay leaf; blend well.
Place pork cubes in a plastic bag or non-metallic bowl.
Pour lime mixture over pork, turning to coat.
Seal bag or cover dish; marinate at least 2 hours or overnight in the refrigerator, turning pork several times.
Remove lime peel, parsley sprigs and Bay leaf from marinade and discard.
Remove pork from marinade, reserving marinade.
Drain pork well.
Heat oil in large skillet over high heat.
Add brown sugar; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add pork cubes; cook and stir about 5 minutes or until pork is browned. Reduce heat to low.
Add onion, tomatoes, bell peppers and reserved marinade; simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until pork is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Spray bottom of pan with Pam or I Can't Believe It's Not Butter.
Crumble raw hamburger in bottom of pan.
Add all the other ingredients, layer upon layer.
Put butter on top.
Bake in 10-inch square dish or pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then chopped dates and nuts.
Shape into rolls and chill.
Cut in slices and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Half of the rolls may be frozen for later use.

title: my favorite cheese ball
directions: Set out until room temperature. Mix with hands and form into a ball. Roll in finely chopped pecans. Put cherry on top to make it pretty.

title: cole slaw vinaigrette
directions: Whisk together oil, vinegar and honey. Place cole slaw mix in medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Pour vinaigrette over mix and toss lightly to coat; cover. Refrigerate. Makes 4 servings.

title: nutty yam bake
directions: Can use canned yams, or boil fresh yams until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add sugar, butter and spices.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Turn into 3-quart greased casserole.

title: cranberry orange muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Grease a muffin tin.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, and orange rind.
Stir to mix.
In a medium bowl, combine egg, orange juice, milk and oil.
Mix well. Add to the flour mixture. Mix just until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in cranberries and pecans.
Spoon into muffin cups, filling about 2/3 full.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center of muffin comes out clean. Remove from pan immediately.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: granola
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Mix the honey, oil and water well and add to dry mixture. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Stir frequently.
May be eaten as is or mixed with other cereals.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, chilies and sour cream.
Spread on tortillas. Alternate shredded chicken, grated cheese and onions.
Roll and place in a greased, covered pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Save some sour cream and cheese to spread over top.
Can be made in morning.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter, cinnamon and salt.
Mix until blended.
Pour onto crust; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: orange sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and orange drinks together.
Put in ice cream freezer and freeze.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add celery and onion.
Saute until tender. Lightly grease a casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Take out 1 cup of cake mix for top of cake.
Mix remainder with oleo and egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients except nuts.
Chill 3 hours. Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: kahlua
directions: Put water, sugar and coffee in a saucepan on low heat. Let simmer for 30 minutes. Stir off and on. Do not boil. Let cool. Skim foam off top. Then add vodka and vanilla. Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: salmon salad
directions: Boil, drain and chill macaroni.
Chop vegetables and add amounts to your taste.
Add salmon.
Mix all together with Miracle Whip.
Top with cherry tomatoes or tomato wedges.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine soups, water, butter and mushrooms in saucepan.
Heat and stir over medium heat.
When warm and thoroughly blended, remove 1 cup of mixture and set aside.
Add rice to saucepan and stir.
Pour mixture of rice and soup into 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Place chicken pieces on top.
Pour remaining cup of soup mixture over chicken pieces.
Cover dish and place in preheated oven at 350°.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans in salted water; drain (if using canned beans, omit salt).
Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can of onions; pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with the rest of the onions and pimentos; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake 1 hour or longer at 350° in greased tube or loaf pan (tube pan is much better).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Remove skin from chicken and place in pan close together.
Salt and pepper.
Spread a thin layer of sour cream over chicken.
Crush the Cheez-Its crackers to make 1 to 2 cups of crumbs.
Sprinkle these over the chicken.
Melt the margarine and drizzle over chicken.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: presidents choice
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Brown in 2 tablespoons fat. Remove chicken and place into casserole dish.
Brown onion slightly in same skillet.
Simmer remaining ingredients in skillet for 30 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oriental broccoli slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice and sugar to boil; cook until tender.
Take egg yolks and beat until smooth.
Add milk to eggs.
Take 1 cup of rice and add to egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Add mixture to rest of rice.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Cook
potatoes
until
tender.
Mix
soup,
sour cream, onions,
mayonnaise and parsley flakes together.
Put potatoes in baking dish; pour mixture over potatoes. Sprinkle bacon on top and bake at 350° for an hour.
For first 30 minutes baking time, cover
with
foil.
Cook,
uncovered,
the remaining 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut meat up into small pieces.
Heat shortening in a large pot on the stove.
Add meat, turning often till brown.
Add sliced onion to the last 5 minutes of browning.
When brown, sprinkle with 1 tsp. salt and pepper.
Add water, cover and heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer until meat is done, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add more water if needed.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Melt 1 stick butter in pan; pour batter over butter.
Add water to pie filling; pour over batter.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar on top and nutmeg to taste (do not stir).
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and place in oblong baking dish. Sprinkle crackers mixed in melted margarine on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef or sausage.
Stir in pizza sauce.
Cook over low heat until mixture is warmed through.

title: "hamburger corn casserole"
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Cook until beef is tender. Remove from heat and add corn, sour cream, soups, pimentos and noodles.
Mix well and pour into a large casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice krispy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Blend eggs and milk in large bowl. Place Rice Krispies in large Ziploc bag, releasing all air. Use rolling pin to mash Rice Krispies completely. Dip each piece of chicken in egg/milk mixture, then in bag of Rice Krispies, then place on a large baking sheet.
Use butter or oil and distribute evenly into pan of chicken. Bake at 350° until chicken is done and Rice Krispies are brown. Serves 4 people.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix well and stuff celery stalks.
Dust with paprika.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and prick several times with a fork.
Bake at 400 degrees for 1 hour or until done.
While potatoes are baking, chop onions.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Set aside.
Allow potatoes to cool; cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 tbsp. green onions, 1/2 c. bacon and 1 cup cheese.
Cook until thoroughly heated; stir in sour cream.
Add extra milk if necessary, for desired thickness.
Serve with remaining onion, bacon and cheese on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease, flour and line tube pan with wax paper.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, beat thoroughly.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and milk to creamed mixture (alternating flour and milk, mixing well).
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.
Use toothpick test to determine doneness.

title: good easy casserole
directions: In electric skillet, slice 3 or 4 potatoes.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup of raw rice, salt and pepper.
Add 3 or 4 sliced carrots and chopped onion.
Crumble raw hamburger on top.
Add cream of mushroom soup and half can water.
Let cook an hour or so at 300° to 325° until potatoes stuck with fork are done.

title: quick and easy chicken casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Dice chicken and mix with soup and water.
Set aside.
Add melted margarine and broth to stuffing mix.
Layer chicken and stuffing mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan beginning and ending with stuffing.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: easy caramel pecan rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt 5 tablespoons of butter in oven.
Stir in brown sugar, water and pecans.
Separate each can of rolls into 4 triangles; seal perforations.
Spread with 3 tablespoons of butter.
Combine cinnamon and sugar.
Sprinkle over buttered dough.
Starting at shorter side, roll up each triangle.
Cut each roll into 4 slices forming 32 pieces.
Place cut side down in pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Invert immediately to remove from pan; serve warm.

title: glazed blue cheese meatballs
directions: Combine beef with Blue cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and seasoned salt.
Make into 12 meatballs.
Melt butter in skillet and brown meatballs on all sides.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Remove meatballs and add cream to drippings. Cook over medium to high heat, stirring for 2 minutes.
Spoon glaze over meatballs.

title: potato bread starter
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Add flour and other dry ingredients. Put into 2 greased loaf pans or 4 small loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (in big pans); less for the small loaf pans.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Dust with flour/pepper mixture.
In large skillet, brown meat in margarine.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; brown lightly.
Stir in beef consomme.
Cover and cook about 1 hour until meat is tender; stir now and then.
Gradually stir in sour cream.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: staked fish
directions: Make a	point
on
one	end
of
a cut green stick (not oleander)
for each fish, about 4-inches longer than the fish. Tie the
fish to the stick at both the head and gills with the head toward
the
pointed end.
Push the stick into the ground next to the
coals	with the head touching the ground.
Grill for 10 minutes.

title: crunchy spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Serve on crackers, fresh vegetables or in rye loaf with bread crumbs hollowed and cut in cubes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add to sugar and stir until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and other ingredients until smooth.
Bake in greased 8 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: basic pot roast(crock-pot)
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Heat shortening in skillet and brown meat on all sides.
Place half of vegetables in bottom of cooker; add meat, then add all other vegetables and liquid. Cook on low 10 to 12 hours or on high 5 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: upside-down cobbler
directions: Heat fruit with juice, berries are best.
Mix other ingredients in pan or bowl you plan to bake in.
Pour the fruit mixture over the batter.
When it is baked, the fruit will be on the bottom and the cake on top.
Watch the ingredients carefully as there is no egg in it, only the butter the size of an egg. It's fun to make and saves on cleaning up bowls.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos; set aside.
Mix butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy, set aside.
Combine milk, pudding and Cool Whip in large bowl; beat this mixture into cream cheese mixture until smooth.
Layer pudding and Oreos, saving some for top. Refrigerate.

title: tomato soup spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a 5 x 9-inch pan and flour.
Measure dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add soup and shortening.
Beat at low speed or medium for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and water and beat 2 more minutes.
Scrape sides and bottom constantly.
Fold in 1 cup chopped nuts and raisins.
Pour into pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack. Frost with cream cheese frosting if desired.

title: potato croquettes(crocke di patate)
directions: Boil potatoes with skins in salted water until tender.
Drain. Peel.
Mash until smooth.
Let it cool.
In a bowl, mix potatoes, cheese, egg, garlic, parsley, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Form into oval-shaped croquettes.
Roll in flour.
Heat olive oil in large skillet and saute croquettes until golden brown on both sides.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until smooth (with mixer).
Pour into pie crust and chill several hours before serving.

title: mixed fruit with amaretto cream
directions: Wash and cap strawberries; cut large ones in half.
Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Place fruit in a large bowl. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar; refrigerate until serving time.

title: corn and pea salad
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients.
Set aside to cool.
Drain corn and peas.
Chop pimento, bell pepper, celery and onion.
Pour cooled syrup over vegetables, stir and refrigerate.

title: pea salad
directions: Let set overnight; drain and serve.

title: frozen fruitcake salad
directions: Blend together sour cream, dessert topping, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in fruits and nuts.
Turn into a 4 1/2-cup ring mold.
Freeze overnight.
Unfold on lettuce.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Spread sauerkraut evenly in skillet.
Cover with onion.
Top with the meat (crumbled).
Salt and pepper.
Pour in the tomato juice.
Cover; cook on low heat until the rice is tender.
If the mixture is too dry, you may add more tomato juice.
Serves about 6 people.

title: cheesecake style pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with pie filling or fresh fruit.

title: flaky pastry for pot pie
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening with a pastry cutter. Stir in water, one teaspoon at a time, briskly with a fork, until it holds together.
On a lightly floured board, roll out.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar slowly. Add salt, creaming well. Add flour and vanilla and then add nuts. Shape into round balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Do not brown. Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: janet's good morning rolls
directions: Arrange rolls in a greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over top.
Cook butter and remaining ingredients over low heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture bubbles.
Pour over rolls. Cover tightly with foil and let stand on countertop overnight.

title: no-drip popsicles
directions: You will need drinking straws.

title: ham and egg quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread #3
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger; mix well and set aside.

title: hummus
directions: In a food processor or blender, combine first five ingredients and blend.
Drizzle in olive oil with processor running.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Put butter in pan.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Add ground beef, brown and drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Layer Veg-All, mushroom soup, then Tater Tots on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: stewed chicken and dumplings
directions: Add water to cover chicken and cook until tender.
Remove and debone.
Heat broth and add dumpling and the chunky chicken.

title: apple pudding
directions: Place apples in deep 8-inch casserole; add lemon juice and water.
Mix cinnamon with 1/2 of the sugar, sprinkle over the apples.
Combine remaining sugar with flour and salt; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over apples and pat smooth.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Yields 10 servings.

title: granny bea's potato salad
directions: Peel large potatoes.
Cut into chunks and boil in salt water until tender.
Dip out of water and put in bowl and set bowl in refrigerator until potatoes cool.
Chop onion, green pepper, pickles and eggs and add to cooler potatoes.
Add a small amount of pickle juice.
Add mayo, mustard, pepper and sugar to taste.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain thoroughly. Spray baking dish with cooking spray or butter dish. Place broccoli in the baking dish. Mix soup, cheese, milk, mayonnaise and egg. Pour over broccoli. Top with Ritz crackers or the bread crumbs mixed with the melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and the crumbs are lightly browned. Serves 6.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar, salt, shortening and flavoring together 3 minutes, about 450 strokes by hand.
Add hot water.
Beat well after adding each egg.
Sift dry ingredients in 4 parts alternately with milk in 3 parts.
Beat after each addition only until smooth.
Turn into two 9-inch round pans, the bottoms of which are covered with oiled waxed paper.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Frost with favorite icing.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix milk and soup together.
Line a 2 quart baking dish with potatoes.
Pour
soup
mixture
in and put onions on top. Place pork
chops on onions.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done.
Put in casserole and pour cream of celery soup and water chestnuts over the broccoli. During the last 10 or 15 minutes of baking time, spread onion rings on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: katie barnes' knobby apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg, vanilla, apples and nuts.
Add the remaining dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch cake pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana pudding #2
directions: Mix 2 beaten egg yolks with 1/4 cup milk in saucepan.
Add pudding mix; blend.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups milk gradually.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens. Remove from heat and cool.
Alternate vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding in baking dish, holding back a portion of the pudding for the top.
Beat 2 egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar, beating.
Pile on pudding.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise.
Line an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with the Twinkies, cream side up.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add drained pineapple and softened ice cream to the Jell-O; mix well by hand.
Pour mixture over Twinkies. Refrigerate until set, then top with whipped topping.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: cheesy sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet. Drain and place in slow cooker. Add cheese. Pour salsa over top. Cover. Cook on low 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serve with tortilla chips or party rye bread.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Add milk and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla and pour into individual custard cups. Place in pan containing 1/2-inch warm water.
Bake in 325°
oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamed seafood delight
directions: Perfect white sauce:
Melt 4 tablespoons butter, stir in 1/4 cup flour, then 3 cups milk; stir until desired thickness and set aside (thinner is preferred).

title: vanilla pie filling
directions: Cook over low heat until thick, then add vanilla and butter.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut raw broccoli and cauliflower in small pieces.
Mix with onion, raisins and fried crumbled bacon; set aside.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli and cauliflower and chill.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and put pecans in bottom.
Place 20 rolls on pecans.
Put dry pudding over rolls.
Melt butter and brown sugar and pour over rolls.
Cover with wax paper.
Put in cold oven overnight.
In morning, take out and preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 25 minutes (check your oven).
Take out and turn out on a cookie sheet.

title: susan's turketti
directions: Cook spaghetti as package directs; drain.
Place turkey, pimentos, green pepper and onion in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour in mushroom soup and turkey broth; add salt, pepper, 1 1/4 cups of grated cheese and spaghetti.
With two forks, lightly toss until all is well mixed and coated with sauce.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese on top of turkey mixture; refrigerate.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked crust.
Makes two pies.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown and done.

title: pomodori a la riso
directions: Cut off tops of tomatoes; scoop out pulp.
Place pulp in sieve; squeeze out juices.
Reserve juice; discard pulp.
Combine rice, parsley, basil, garlic and salt.
Add enough juice to moisten the mixture.
Spoon back into the hollow tomatoes.
Add remaining juice.
Place tomatoes on pan greased with 1/2 of the olive oil.
Replace tomato tops; drizzle the tomatoes with remaining oil.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1/2 hour, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 1/2 hour.

title: applesauce balls
directions: Simmer applesauce gently 5 minutes.
Add sugar, butter, cocoa and salt.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add oats, nuts, vanilla and almond.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
When cool, roll into balls and then in pecan meal. Store in airtight container.
Yield:
50 to 55 balls.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Mix flour and seasonings together. Melt butter in skillet on medium heat. Coat chicken breasts in flour mixture and cook in butter until brown on both sides. Place in baking dish. Mix sour cream, soup (do not add water) and mushrooms. Spread on top of chicken and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Add cheese and put back in oven until melted. Serve over rice if you wish.

title: brownie drops
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Cool.
Beat eggs and gradually add sugar, about 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat until thick.
Blend in chocolate and butter.
Sift dry ingredients and blend with other ingredients.
Add coconut.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350°
for 12 minutes.
Makes about 40.

title: home made ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well and combine with enough 2% milk to fill freezer to the fill line. Freeze as directed in electric ice cream freezer.

title: really good dill pickles
directions: Boil the vinegar, water and salt. Pour over cucumbers which have been washed and packed in jars with other ingredients. Don't open for
2 months.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 minutes in 300° oven. Mix 3 Tbsp. brown sugar and 3 Tbsp. ketchup and put on top of meat loaf.
Bake another 30 minutes or until done.

title: cherry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, vanilla and almond extract.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; mix well.
Stir in flour sifted with baking powder.
Spread 3/4 batter on greased cookie sheet.
Spread with pie filling.
Drop rest of the batter by teaspoonful over cherry pie filling.
Dribble frosting while warm.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream; continue beating.
Add flavorings.
Turn into a greased and floured tube cake pan; bake at 325° for 55 minutes, or until done.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together, except bacon. Pour into a 2 quart baking dish. Top with bacon strips. Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add partially thawed strawberries.
Stir.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and chill.

title: "blueberry treat"
directions: Spoon blueberries into shells.
Add Cool Whip and enjoy!

title: greek potato salad
directions: Mix cooled, cooked potatoes with all ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: lorraine's fajitas
directions: Note:
Serve with Ortega taco sauce, sour cream and Pace picante sauce.
This chicken mixture should fill 6 to 9 tortillas.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Mix all together by hand.
Chill 2 hours.
Form into balls and roll in additional chopped walnuts.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread over flour tortillas.
Roll and cut into serving pieces.
Dip in picante sauce for serving.

title: sweet potato-raisin patties
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Beat in egg and salt.
Add flour only if potatoes are wet.
Mix in raisins.
Drop mixture from a tablespoon on heated greased frying pan.
Brown slowly on both sides.
Makes about 12 patties.

title: catfish creole
directions: Heat oil in a large pan.
Add flour and stir until brown.
Add some water gradually with stirring.
Add all ingredients, except fish and rice.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add fish and simmer additional 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: snappy green beans
directions: Fry bacon lightly.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until soft.
Add remaining ingredients; heat through.
Serve at once. Serves 4 to 6.

title: busy day goulash skillet
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients in a large skillet. Cook until beef is brown and vegetables are tender. Drain off excess fat. Add remaining ingredients, except
macaroni and cook on low heat for 20 minutes. Add macaroni and cook 10 minutes longer.
If desired, serve with grated cheese and a dollop of sour cream. Serves 4 to 6.

title: grits casserole
directions: Combine grits and water.
Mix with remaining ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked flounder and tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place flounder in buttered baking pan; drizzle butter or margarine over surface.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread onion over fish.
Scatter basil over onion.
Top with sliced tomatoes.
In a small bowl, combine mustard, cayenne and wine; pour into baking pan.

title: texas caviar
directions: Rinse beans in cold water.
In 5-quart Dutch oven, put beans and 6 cups water.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let sit 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans, then put back into Dutch oven with 6 more cups water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together with beans; toss to coat.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: tasty chicken breasts
directions: Split chicken breasts into 2 halves.
Hammer or "pound" breasts until thin.
Place in dish and cover with Italian dressing.
Soak for 1 to 2 hours (refrigerate while soaking). Cook on grill or bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with green onions.
This is good with rice.

title: crunch top broccoli bake
directions: Heat margarine in small saucepan until melted.
Stir in flour, salt, sugar, pepper and onions.
Add sour cream; stir until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to just boiling point.
Fold in broccoli.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Toss together the cereal and cheese; sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: spaggetti(kids kitchen)
directions: Get noodles and tomato stuff in a can.
Get some lettus and get you some tomatoes and get some salad dressing on it.
Then you wind the winder up what goes ding.
When it goes ding, tick, tick, tick when it goes ding it's ready.

title: roast-n-red gravy
directions: Brown roast on both sides.
Season to taste, then add ketchup and water.
Add potatoes and onion.
Cook on medium until roast is tender.
Add extra water during cooking as needed to thin gravy.

title: whipped cream horseradish sauce(great with prime rib or roast!!)
directions: Whip cream until stiff peaks form.
Fold in seasoned salt, Tabasco and very well drained horseradish.
Yields 1 cup.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, pineapple and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack. When cooled, frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Refrigerate until slightly thick.
Cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add jello and mix well. Whip Milnot in bowl until real stiff.
Fold into jello and cream cheese mixture.
Pour on graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Heat milk and cook cabbage in it for 2 minutes. Add blended flour, butter and salt. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly. The cabbage retains its crispness and is delicate in flavor and color.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery; cook slowly for 20 minutes. Cook rice is salted water; drain with cool water.
Combine all ingredients; bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: granddaddy dosses' barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Heat and taste.
If not enough, add Worcestershire sauce and red pepper.
If too hot, add ketchup.

title: cherry squares
directions: Work mixture into crumbs with clean hands.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups for topping.
Press remaining crumbs into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Spoon over hot crust 1 can of cherry pie filling.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Return to oven and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana shrimp curry
directions: Cook onion over low heat in butter until clear and golden. Add curry powder and milk.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; add bananas. Cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot fluffy rice and hot shrimp.
Accompany with flaked coconut, chutney and chopped peanuts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Trim crusts from day-old bread and cut bread into narrow strips.
Place strips and crusts on a cookie sheet in a 200° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until bread is crisp.
Remove and cool.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle chopped pecans evenly in the bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits in quarters; roll each piece in sugar mixture and layer in pan.

title: corn stuffing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Will stuff up to a 20 pound turkey or bake in casserole dish, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pinwheel snacks
directions: Chop corned beef very small.
Mix with soft cream cheese.
Lay out dough and spread on cream mixture.
Roll up like jelly roll. Cut into even slices and put on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baruschis
directions: Scald milk and let it cool until lukewarm.
Soak yeast in warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let set 5 minutes.
Add yeast to cooled milk.
Add 3 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Let stand 30 minutes, then add eggs, sugar, salt and oil.
Mix all together and add 5 to 5 1/2 cups more flour.
Knead dough until smooth. Keep adding a little oil in bottom of pan to dough from pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.

title: garlic baked chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Lay flat (1 layer) in baking dish. Put 1 slice of
butter
on
each
piece.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and Season-All salt.
Cover
with foil and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes to
hour.
Remove
foil
and bake about 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together in baking dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top and
spread melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger, then add all other ingredients and cook for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: summer lemon pie(by a good friend, kathy klatt.)
directions: Mix the last two ingredients together.
Pour into prepared shells and refrigerate for 1 day. Cool and refreshing dessert for a hot summer day.

title: ratatouille
directions: Put oil in skillet.
Over low heat, saute in order the squash, zucchini, onion, pepper, celery and eggplant.
Stir over low heat until partially cooked. Add tomato sauce and cook for 15 minutes. Place in casserole or individual casserole dishes. Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Heat in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
May be frozen for future use. Defrost and heat as previous.
Excellent hot or cold. Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Soak apples and bananas in lemon juice to keep them from turning dark.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Prepare the day before and mix up kool-aid using sugar and water.
Mix well and store in refrigerator, and put some in ice trays.
When ready to use mix pineapple juice & ginger ale together with kool-aid and serve.

title: raisin bread muffins(3 weeks supply)
directions: Store in a covered container and refrigerate. Bake for 20 minutes at 400° in a greased muffin pan.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Wrap chicken in foil and bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour. Cool and bone; cut in large pieces.
Put 3/4 cup of the broth from the chicken in bottom of casserole.
Add salt to taste.

title: hoppin john(good luck dish for new year's day)
directions: Cook rice.
Fry and drain bacon.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Drain peas, saving juice for later.
Add peas to sauteed onion.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir in cooked rice.
Add 2 tablespoons of vinegar with 1/2 teaspoon of sugar in it.
Add juice from can of peas to moisten.
Garnish with chopped bacon.

title: chinese noodle bake
directions: Chop onions and celery. Brown with hamburger. Add rest of the ingredients and bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Put hard noodles on top and bake 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: dirty shrimp
directions: In heavy skillet, melt margarine.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic, peppers, salt, thyme, basil and oregano.
Cook 1 minute. Add shrimp.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring to coat shrimp evenly. Add beer.
Cover and cook 1 minute.

title: tangy topped salmon
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread on topping and bake 10 more minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat together the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until well mixed. Set aside.

title: congealed ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Chill until firm. This is good anytime, but I always make it at Christmas.

title: alaska king's bread
directions: *Or use your favorite biscuit recipe.

title: congo bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
In a bowl, combine the melted butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. beaten well after each.
Add the dry ingredients, nuts and chips.
Mix well and put in pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until toothpick comes out clean from center. (Makes 32 squares.)

title: tuna lasagne(makes 8 servings)
directions: Saute the mushrooms, green pepper and onion in the margarine. Blend in the tomato sauce and paste, Cheddar cheese, spices and tuna.
Cook noodles.

title: aunt nellie's prune cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Sift flour with salt, soda and spices.
Add alternately with buttermilk to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add prunes and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until cake tests done. Cool in pan.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix in other ingredients.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.
Use a sheet cake pan or baking dish.

title: whiskey slush
directions: If you can't get at it with sandpaper, old glue can be softened up with ordinary household vinegar.
All traces of vinegar should be rinsed away with fresh water and the wood allowed to become dry before fresh glue is applied.

title: round steak and rich gravy
directions: Mix soups and water. Layer service size pieces of meat and soup in the crock-pot. Cook on high for a couple of hours. Reduce heat to low and cook for the rest of the day. Makes its own gravy.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey glazed snack
directions: In large bowl, combine cereal, pretzels and nuts.
In saucepan, melt butter (over low heat); add honey and cinnamon and flavorings.
Pour over cereal mixture and toss.
Spread on 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Stir occasionally; cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken fry potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Mix Miracle Whip, chopped eggs, relish, onion, celery seed, sugar and shredded carrots.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Serves 50 to 75 people generously.

title: "easy children's cookies"
directions: Mix all together.
Spoon onto cookie sheet, patting down a little.
Cook at 325°.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: brown pudding sauce(good on fruit cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into saucepan and cook slowly until thickened.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix everything together and heat until sauce is clear and thick.
Serve.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Brown ground beef, stirring until completely done; drain well. Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until meat absorbs most of liquid.
Place a generous serving on a hamburger bun.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled for large groups.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue burgers
directions: Lightly brown beef. Add onion and celery; saute. Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and pour over meat mixture.
Cover pan. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chinese mustard sauce
directions: Stir boiling water into dry mustard.
Add salt and salad oil. Serve on egg roll, fried shrimp, etc.

title: polish noodles and cabbage
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onion and sausage until onion is transparent.
Add cabbage and saute 5 minutes or until tender but still crisp.
Stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper.

title: chess pie
directions: Sprinkle coconut in pie shell. Melt butter; add sugar. Beat eggs with sugar. Add vanilla. Pour over coconut.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes; turn oven down to 275°. Bake 1 1/2 hours until top is golden brown.
Let cool.

title: italian stuffed chicken(makes 4 servings)
directions: With a meat mallet, pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness. Place in large baking pan.
Add oil-vinegar dressing and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Remove chicken pieces and drain.
Cut each piece in half crosswise.
Place cheese, tomato slices and a pinch of basil on each of 4 pieces of chicken. Top each with remaining half of breast.
Pound edges together to seal.

title: oatmeal-mushroom patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drop by tablespoonful into hot oil and brown on each side over medium heat.
Place in casserole dish; cover with 1 (10 ounce) can of cream of celery or mushroom soup (This is a second can).
Add 1/2 cup water or liquid from canned mushrooms and 1 1/2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly using an electric mixer. grease two 9 X 5 X 3 inch loaf pans.
pour batter into pans and bake at 350 for 1 hour.
Cool on wire racks.

title: cucumber tea sandwiches
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Squeeze excess moisture from cucumbers and add to cream cheese mixture. Spread on bread shapes and garnish.

title: tuna chow-mein casserole
directions: Chop celery, onion and green pepper.
In small skillet, melt butter and saute celery, onion and green pepper.
Mix into skillet the cashews, tuna, milk, water, soup, pepper and 1 cup noodles. Pour mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spread remaining noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot fruit(relish)
directions: Drain fruit and mix all ingredients together.
Dot with butter and bake in shallow dish at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ruth's crab boats
directions: Halve potatoes.
Scrape out potato; reserve skins.
Whip butter, milk, salt, pepper, onion and cheese with electric mixer. Add potato prep and mix thoroughly.
Fold in crab meat.
Refill skins and sprinkle with paprika.
Reheat at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix 1/3 cup of hot chocolate mix for 1 cup of hot water.

title: chocolate marshmallow drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cocoa and blend alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts.
Bake 7 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and press marshmallow in half, cut side down, on each cookie.
Return to oven 4 minutes; cool and spread with icing.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Melt the butter to approximately 165° so that it separates and leaves the whey on the bottom of the pan.
Beat the egg yolks with the white wine and place over the double boiler.
Use only the clarified butter, not any of the sediment type.
Add slowly the butter until you find the liaison of butter and egg yolks.
If you find the butter and egg yolks are too thick, add a little iced water to thin.
When you find the liaison is of a creamy consistency, serve!

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: "everyone wants this recipe" casserole
directions: Cook bacon crisp; drain and crumble.
Reserve bacon drippings and saute onions, then mushrooms.
In large mixing bowl, combine bacon, onions, mushrooms, seasonings, cheese, eggs and milk.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: apricot pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix
all
ingredients, except walnuts.	Pour and spread batter onto
a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle the walnuts on top
of the
batter.
Bake	at
for
15 minutes.
After baking, immediately flip sheet cake over onto a towel or waxed paper
that is
sprinkled
with confectioners sugar.
Slowly, roll the
cake with the towel from one end to the other while it is warm.	Let cool.

title: carrot bread
directions: Beat well the eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and walnuts.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients well and bake in 2 large loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Slice carrots diagonally after you have cleaned and peeled (about 5 or 6 cups) and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Cool and drain.
Blend soup, oil, vinegar and sugar well.
Add rest of ingredients, pour over carrots.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: sugarless apple pie(diabetic recipe)
directions: Bring juice to a boil.
Add apples and cook 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with a little water.
Add to apples; cool.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 400° for 30 minutes.

title: meat stuffed peppers
directions: Remove seeds from peppers, parboil 5 minutes and drain.
Brown meat and onions in fat.
Add tomatoes, corn and seasoning and top with butter and bread crumbs.
Stand up in a greased 11 x7-inch pan.
