Add small amount of water to cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or 375°.

title: best cookies ever
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugars.
Mix in the eggs and vanilla extract.
Mix in the flour, oats, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Roll dough into small balls (no larger than ping pong ball size).
Place about 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: easy asparagus casserole
directions: Place asparagus in casserole. Mix soup, juice, salt and pepper and pour over asparagus. Sprinkle with cheese. Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs. Sprinkle over cheese. Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: super corn
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix melted butter, pecans and flour and press in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix pudding according to directions and layer over cream cheese.
Top with Cool Whip and pecans.

title: mother's chocolate syrup
directions: Add first 3 ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Continue to heat (low) while filling hot jars.
Seal.

title: gina's quick vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and drain; add onion, garlic salt and other seasoning salts.
In large pot, start soup with cans of tomato sauce (equal amounts of water), vegetables and meat.
Bring to a boil and add macaroni.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until the macaroni is done.
It's good with Jiffy cornbread.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Heat potatoes until hot, then pour off liquid.
Combine potatoes with sugar, eggs, oleo, milk, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Whip with mixer until smooth.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole and bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Make topping.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients, only adding enough milk for a thick batter.
Put into hot fat by dropping a teaspoonful at a time. Fry until golden brown.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown soup bones and chuck cubes in Dutch oven for 2 hours with water, onion and seasonings.
Add vegetables, tomato paste, cabbage and water.
Simmer 5 hours.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour until combined.
Add cream and chicken broth all at once; stir until smooth.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat; add the cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in macaroni, chicken, pimientos, salt and pepper. Add additional broth if needed.
Pour into a 3-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through. Serves 6 to 8.

title: three corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish, mixing well. Bake at 375° 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown and set in center.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix together like pie dough the butter, flour and chopped nuts, will be stiff.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Combine eggs, milk and butter. Stir in nuts and chips. Pour into pie crust. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool. Best if served at room temperature with caramel topping. Refrigerate leftovers. Servings: 8.

title: cheese roll
directions: Set cheese out to soften.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for 25 minutes. If you desire, halfway through baking, top with 1 1/2 ounces of sliced pepperoni and 1/2 cup sliced ripe olives.
Continue to bake the remainder of time.
Serve hot with Tostitos chips.
Great!
(I add the pepperoni and olives.)

title: quick roast beef
directions: Put roast in baking dish.
Add pepper, mushrooms and onion soup.
Cover and bake at 350° until roast is tender.
Add potatoes and carrots and bake 30 more minutes.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 tablespoon butter, crouton crumbs and dinner rolls to make filling.
Spread out dinner rolls and add 1/4 mixture to center of four rolls.
Top with another dinner roll.
Pinch edges together.
Brush with reserved melted butter and dip in crouton crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 4.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: candied pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and boil until it spins a thread. Pour over pecans in a large bowl or put pecans in pan and coat real good. Spread out on wax paper to cool.

title: stir-fry cabbage
directions: Put oil in large
skillet on high temperature of stove. Add cabbage, sugar, salt
and pepper.
Stir continuously until cabbage is limp.
Don't overcook.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine eggs and oil together.
Mix flour with seasonings.
Dip chicken pieces in eggs; roll in flour and then roll in corn flakes. Line baking pan with heavy aluminum foil.
Place chicken in pan, stacking boney side down.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add pineapple and saute.
Mix pineapple juice, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard together. Pour over sauteed mixture; simmer for 30 minutes.
Tastes great over rice.

title: granola mix
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix first five dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, water, oil, honey, molasses, cinnamon and vanilla in saucepan.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Do not boil. Pour syrup over dry ingredients.
Stir until well coated.
Spread onto cookie sheet.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool and add dry fruit. Keep stored in airtight container.

title: quick boston cream cake
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in medium saucepan.
Blend well. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill.
Split cake layers horizontally to make 4 thin layers.
Beat pudding until creamy.
Spread about 2/3 cup on each layer and stack.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Cook onion in oil in large saucepan over medium heat until tender.
Add ginger and pumpkin pie spice; cook for 1 minute.
Add squash and apple juice; heat to boil.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 15-20 minutes or until squash is tender.
Puree soup in blender or food processor in batches, until smooth. Return to saucepan; heat through.
Serve soup hot or chilled with crackers.
For thinner soup, add water to desired consistency.

title: microwave mini pizza
directions: Layer sauce, cheeses and pepperoni over crackers.
Microwave 30 seconds on High.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, raisins and nuts.
Mix in carrots.
Pour in cake pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: easy delicious pie crust for lemon pie
directions: Cut margarine into baking mix until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk until mixture begins to form a ball and cleans sides of bowl.
Pat dough on bottom of ungreased pie dish or pan and work on top to sides and rim.
Bake until done at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and mold into a loaf.
Bake at 375 degrees for approximately 40 minutes.
After 30 minutes, take meat loaf out of oven and cover it with ketchup.
Put it back in oven and bake it for 10 more minutes.

title: spinach-stuffed mushrooms(serves 4)
directions: Lightly coat an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with cooking spray and set aside.
Place spinach in a medium size heavy saucepan with just the water that clings to the leaves; cook, covered, over moderate heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until wilted.
Drain and cool, then with your hands, squeeze out liquid.
Chop fine and set aside.
Heat oven to 400°.

title: gazpacho
directions: Soak bread for about 10 minutes in 1 quart of the water.
Take bread out and put in a large bowl with tomatoes, garlic, olive oil, vinegar, salt, white pepper, chunks of cucumber, green pepper and the yolks of the hard-boiled eggs.
Put 1/3 of the mixture into blender with 1/4 cup of the water from the soaked bread.
Run on high speed for 10 seconds or until smooth.
Repeat process on high speed until the ice is dissolved.
Add to soup. Refrigerate for at least one hour.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Melt marshmallows with sugar and milk. Cook until melted. Remove from heat. Add coconut. Mix well. Set aside.

title: hidden valley ranch crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all together and chill.
Crumbled bacon may be added to garnish.

title: strawberry surprise cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften cheese to room temperature. Press cottage cheese through a sieve or food processor.
Using mixer, mix cottage cheese, cream cheese and salt.
Prepare frosting mix as directed.
Add frosting mix to cheeses, blending well.
Add 1 teaspoon grated lemon rind.
Pour into prepared crust and bake 35 minutes.
Upon removal from oven, carefully spread surface with sour cream.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill and serve with crushed strawberries on top.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream butter, eggs and powdered sugar; beat until fluffy and spread over crust by tablespoons. Dissolve jello in hot water; add frozen raspberries and let set until thick.
Then spread over creamy mixture.
Whip cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over raspberries and let stand overnight or all day.

title: chicken with orange and honey sauce
directions: Combine cornstarch, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake to coat.
Remove chicken, save cornstarch.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in large skillet.
Add chicken and brown (approximately 5 minutes).
Add the rest of butter, turn chicken and brown the other side; transfer to plate.
Dissolve cornstarch in the chicken broth.
Whisk the broth, o.j., mustard and honey into the pan drippings.
Bring to boil stirring constantly over medium heat.
Return chicken, lower heat to medium low and cover. Cook approximately 8 to 10 minutes until chicken is opaque. Divide chicken and sauce among 4 plates.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar
and
vanilla
in a medium mixing bowl. Beat well.
Add
eggs
and
beat
well.
Stir in flour. Gradually stir in chocolate chips, pecans and coconut; pour in pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: brownie cookies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water in double boiler, then cool. Beat eggs and shortening together well.
Add sugar; beat until well mixed.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured pan that is 9 x 5-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Brush bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with oil.
Mix Parmesan cheese, flour and seasonings; coat chicken.
Arrange skin-side down in pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.
Turn chicken and spread spaghetti sauce on top.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Place oil, eggs and sugar in a large mixing bowl and beat well.
Stir in flour, soda and cinnamon into egg mixture until well blended.
Fold in vanilla, carrots, pineapple, coconut and nuts, blending well.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Have the glaze ready to pour over the hot cake.

title: pepperoni pizza bread
directions: Brush two 11 x 17-inch baking sheets with olive oil.
Divide dough in half.
Roll 1 dough piece out to edges of 1 prepared sheet.
Place half of pepperoni slices in crosswise rows on dough, leaving 1/2-inch borders at ends.
Sprinkle with half of Mozzarella, half of garlic powder, half of basil, half of oregano and half of onion.
Top with half of Parmesan.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: cantonese shrimp and green beans
directions: Thaw frozen shrimp.
Dissolve instant bouillon in boiling water.
Heat oil in a deep skillet.
Cook onions, garlic and shrimp in hot oil over medium heat for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in salt, ginger, pepper and green beans.
Mix well, then cover.
Let simmer for 5 to 8 minutes until beans are crisp cooked.
Stir cornstarch in cold water.
Add to shrimp mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear. Serves 6.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; blend with mixer.
(If mixture is too thick to work with, add some strawberry juice.)
Blend in strawberries and nuts.
Pour into 2, greased and dusted with flour, loaf pans (9 x 5-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken salad with a twist
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions.
Mix cooked chicken and Italian dressing with hot macaroni.
Cool.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and mustard.
Stir in chopped onion, olives, cucumber, celery, pepper and salt (if desired).
Add to macaroni mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: raisin bran cookies
directions: Stir together cereal, flour and soda and set aside.
Beat margarine and sugars; add eggs and beat well.
Stir in cereal and mix well.
Drop tablespoon size onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: corn oil pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add the blended liquid to dry, mixing with a fork.
Press ingredients around side and bottom of 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool; fill with your favorite filling.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and onion juice.
Mix well.
Add oil slowly, beating constantly with electric beater, until mixture becomes thick.
Add poppy seed and beat a few minutes longer.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.
Can be made in blender.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: The night before, cook your sausage; crumble it in the skillet. In a casserole dish, put the sausage, eggs, cheese and crumbled up bread.
Stir them together and place, covered, in your refrigerator.

title: homemade butter
directions: Beat with mixer until smooth
Makes double amount.
Tastes like country homemade butter!

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove the yolks and mash with a fork.
Add the mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, sugar and mustard.
Mix until creamy.
Fill egg whites with the yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cauliflower-broccoli imperial
directions: Leave cauliflower whole.
Cook, covered in lightly salted boiling water 25 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Cut broccoli flowerets from stems and cut stems into thin lengthwise slices.
Cook flowerets and stems, covered, in lightly salted boiling water 10 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain and cook bacon until crisp.	Drain, reserve 3 tablespoons drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion in reserved drippings just until soft.
Stir in brown sugar, vinegar and seasonings. Simmer 3 minutes and spoon about half of broccoli into a heated serving bowl.
Place cauliflower on top and arrange remaining broccoli in a ring around edges.
Pour hot dressing over vegetables and top with bacon.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine butter, cocoa and cola in saucepan.
Heat until boiling.
Add 10x sugar and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Spread on cake.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add 3/4 cup sugar and powdered sugar. Continue beating well. Add vanilla and salt. Line buttered pie pan with brown paper.Dust with flour. Pour mixture onto paper. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° For Filling: Beat the egg yolks slightly on top of double boiler. Stir in 1/2 cup of sugar, lemon juice, rind and salt. Cook over boiling water, stirring until thick, 8 to 10 minutes. When mixture cools, whip the cup of cream and fold into it. Pour into meringue shell and chill for at least 12 hours.Serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first three (3) ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to liquid mixture.
Grate zucchini.
Add to batter along with nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chicken between sheets of waxed paper and pound until 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle one side of chicken each with parsley.
Top with sliced ham and cheese.
Roll up jelly roll fashion; fasten with toothpick.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken. Bone and dice. Saute onion, celery and pepper in butter until tender. Cook noodles in chicken stock; drain, leaving about 1 cup stock in noodles.
Mix the soup, mushrooms and cheese with the sauteed vegetables and chicken. Toss with the noodles, adding more stock if needed.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pat huval's fried shrimp
directions: Clean shrimp.
Make a mixture of eggs, milk, baking powder and vinegar.
Marinate shrimp for at least 1 hour in this mixture. Remove; season lightly with seasoning.
Dip in flour and fry in 380° oil not over 10 minutes.

title: collard salad
directions: Boil collards until real tender. Salt to taste. Chop collards in a chopper (not blender).
Mix all ingredients well. Serve with salad crackers or it makes a delicious sandwich.
Add pepper sauce for flavor, if you desire.

title: picante-cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add picante sauce.
Mix well, then add other ingredients.
Blend.
Add more picante sauce to thickness as desired.

title: chili sauce
directions: Parboil tomatoes.
Remove skin and chop into small pieces. Peel onions and cut and remove seeds from peppers.
Use grinder or food processor to chop up onions and peppers.
Combine everything in an enamel pan and cook from 2 1/2 to 3 hours over low heat.
Can hot; put in hot jars.

title: homemade v-8 juice
directions: Cook tomatoes, celery, onions and green pepper until mushy. Blend in blender.
Add salt and sugar.
Pour into jars to freeze, or can same as tomato juice.

title: a christmas cake from the bible
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heavily grease and flour a 10 inch tube or Bundt pan, or two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: polish sausage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except hot pepper sauce in large kettle. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, simmer 8-10 minutes, stir occasionally. Stir in pepper sauce and add rice. Serve hot.

title: berry delight
directions: Crumble graham crackers and mix with butter (melted).
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust and chill.
Mix Jell-O, cornstarch and sugar and add to boiling water.
Cook until slightly thick.
Remove from heat and refrigerate until thickened, but not solid.
Add berries and pour over cream filling.
Use berries of any kind.

title: peach crumb cake
directions: Divide the yellow cake mix in half (about 2 cups of dry mix is half).
Prepare half the mix, as package directs, using just half the water, egg and shortening called for in the directions. Measure 1 cup of batter and set aside.
Pour remaining batter into greased 9-inch square pan.

title: chicken luau
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Heat oil in skillet and brown.
Stir in garlic and add broth.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, until chicken is tender.
Place in casserole dish and keep warm in oven. Bring broth to a boil and reduce to 2 cups.
Blend cornstarch and water to make paste; stir into broth and cook.
Stir frequently until thick.
Drain spinach and stir spinach and coconut milk into chicken broth.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken and serve.
Serves 8.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill thoroughly and serve.
Best if made 24 hours in advance.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix coconut and pecans together. Sprinkle in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour cake mix in pan on top of nuts.
Melt butter and cheese.
Add slowly powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cinnamon bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and shortening in bowl.
When lukewarm, add yeast and eggs.
Stir until yeast is dissolved.
Beat in 5 cups flour or a little more, so you can handle it.
Roll into 10 x 14-inch rectangle, about 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with 1/4 cup butter, then sprinkle with 2 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon added to 1 cup sugar.
Roll into loaves.
Bake at 350°.
After 30 minutes, cover with foil.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then turn out.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini in salted water until tender.
Drain well and pour into bowl.
Add 1 cup warm water, brown sugar, white sugar, cinnamon and cream of tartar.
Mix well.

title: mini chip pound cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in chips.
Pour into a greased 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool completely.

title: "i remember" floating island
directions: Get a pot of boiling water, then turn down the heat so that water is just under boil, not bubbling at all.
Separate eggs and whip egg whites until very stiff, but not dry.
In other words, the beaten whites will slide around the bowl.
At this point begin to beat in the sugar very gradually and continue beating until whites stand in peaks.

Now, using a tablespoon that has been dipped in cold water, drop the mixture, one tablespoonful at a time, into the pot of water and poach each island for a few minutes, first on one side and then the other.
Don't crowd!
When poached, lift each one from pan with a spoon and place on paper toweling to dry and cool.

title: dunkin cookies
directions: Blend well the butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and flour
(which has been sifted with baking powder and soda).
Add oatmeal, coconut, nuts and cornflakes last (it makes them more crispy).
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dom's succotash(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Soak the lima beans overnight; drain. Place limas, corn and ham in 8-quart saucepan. Add water to cover by 2-inches. Bring to boiling; reduce heat to medium and cook until limas are tender (about 45 minutes). Stir occasionally. Add green beans, onion and red pepper; cook 15 minutes. Drain. Dissolve cornstarch in chicken stock in another saucepan. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook over medium heat until smooth and thickened; whisk constantly. Stir into vegetables.

title: tomato surprise
directions: Pour tomatoes into saucepan (save can to use as mold). Bring to a boil. Add Jell-O and salt, stirring until dissolved. Add vinegar. Cool. Pour into can. Chill until firm. To unmold, puncture bottom of can before dipping in warm water or open bottom of can with can opener and punch out mold.	Serve with mayonnaise, if desired.
Makes about 2 cups, 4 side dishes or 6 relish servings.

title: savory meat balls
directions: Combine beef and next 6 ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls. Brown well in fat in skillet and remove.
Mix water with flour. Stir into drippings.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Add meat. Cook covered for 30 minutes.
If desired, serve on rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chess meringue pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, egg yolks, meal, margarine, Pet milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes and then at 350° for 20 minutes or until pie is set.
When pie is done, add the cream of tartar to the egg whites.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and continue beating until well mixed.
Spread on baked pie and return to 350° oven until meringue is brown.

title: party pizza spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on tiny party rye bread slices.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
This spread refrigerates well and freezes well.

title: baked cheese potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes.
Cut into thin slices, not cutting all the way through.
Place potatoes in baking dish.
Fan slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes more until lightly browned, cheeses melted and potatoes are done.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Remove outer leaves and break cauliflower into flowerets; wash thoroughly.
Layer lettuce, cauliflower and peas in a 3-quart bowl (in that order).

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown onion in 1/2 stick margarine in skillet.
In large mixing bowl, mix hash browns, cheese, soups, sour cream and salt. Add cooked onion.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in skillet, then add corn flakes.
Put potato mixture in 3-quart oblong casserole. Sprinkle cornflakes on top and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken-artichoke casserole
directions: Salt, pepper and paprika the chicken pieces.
Brown in 4 tablespoons butter.
Put into casserole.
In frying pan, saute mushrooms with 2 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over them and stir in consomme and sherry.
While this cooks for 5 minutes, arrange artichokes between chicken pieces.
Pour mushroom-sherry sauce over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut quick cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Combine next 3 ingredients and spread over warm cake.
Sprinkle coconut and broil for 4 minutes to light brown.

title: watermelon sweet pickles
directions: Put in jar.
Pare, cut and weight rinds.
Put in lime water and let remain overnight.
Stir occasionally (8 pounds of rinds makes 1 gallon of pickles).
In morning, wash and soak rinds in several waters.
Cook in boiling water for 1 hour.
Drain in colander.
Make syrup using pound for pound of sugar to rind. Cover sugar with water.
Put rind in sugar to boil hard in covered boiler for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour 1 quart of vinegar on spices in separate boiler to boil for 1/2 hour.
Use any whole spices you like; do not use ground (cinnamon, cloves, allspice, etc.).
Pour vinegar and spices into kettle with rinds and syrup and boil about 1 hour or until syrup thickens.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
I sometimes add green food coloring for colorful Christmas pickles.

title: hummus
directions: In small skillet, gently shake sesame seed over low heat 5 minutes just until golden brown.
In food processor, puree toasted sesame seed, garlic, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup oil until smooth. Add chickpeas, lemon juice and remaining 1/4 cup oil.
Process until smooth.
Stir in parsley.
Serve with pita bread.

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Mix thawed or fresh fruit and yogurt.
Fold in Cool Whip until blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: colache
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onions and saute until softened.
Add zucchini, green beans and pepper; cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: motts quick-n-easy cake
directions: Grease pans.
Prepare cake mix according to directions, except substitute applesauce for oil.
Add 1 tablespoon flour to dry mix. Cook, cool and frost, if desired.

title: cheese-stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Combine onion, parsley, salt, pepper, garlic salt, chopped cheese, bread crumbs and egg in bowl. Mix well. Rinse chicken and pat dry. Place 1 slice cheese on each chicken breast. Top with bread crumb mixture. Roll up to enclose filling, securing with wooden pick. Dip in melted butter; coat with flour and Parmesan cheese. Place in baking pan. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: chicken curry and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Arrange cooked broccoli in buttered 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle almonds over broccoli and arrange chicken in small pieces on next layer.
Mix mayonnaise, soup and curry powder.
Spread over casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: judy's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Stir in oats.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: wanda's taco salad
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix lettuce, tomato, onion rings, cheese, beans, celery and oregano.
Toss well.
Break corn chips into small pieces.
Combine beef, chips and Italian dressing.
Add to salad mixture.
Toss.
Garnish with the parsley.
Serves 6.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: May add anything you'd like.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Stir in marshmallows.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together well.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Mix all together and congeal.

title: filipino chicken marinade
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Let chicken marinate in the sauce for a few hours or overnight.
Keep turning the chicken over. Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours or until tender.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Place mixture on rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: bohemian crumb cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like pie crust and remove 1 cup for topping.
Add egg, baking soda mixture, nuts and vanilla.
Blend together and then pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle with topping mixture.
Bake at 300° for
1 hour.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain pineapple; drain and pit cherries.
Heat juices to boiling and dissolve jello in them.
Cool.
When cool, add Coca-Cola and put in refrigerator to set.
Cut cream cheese in small pieces.
When mixture starts to set, add pineapple, cherries and cream cheese.
Serve as dessert or on lettuce as a salad. Serves 15.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add peaches and simmer 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and allow peaches to cool in liquid. Serve warm or cold as a meat accompaniment or salad.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Drain.
Brown beef with onion and green pepper.
Add mushrooms, pepperoni and spaghetti sauce.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Simmer.
Place noodles in oblong casserole dish.
Spoon sauce over noodles.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is bubbly.

title: mile high biscuits(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven 450 degrees.
grease baking sheet.
Sift flour, baking powder, cream of tartar, sugar, salt into mixing bowl. with pastry blender cut shortening into flour mixture until mixture resembles coarse meal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut up into bite size pieces and place in baking dish 9x11 in.
Mix soups and milk and pour over chicken. Top with stove top bread crumbs.
Mix stove top seasoning as stated on box and pour over casserole.
Bake 375 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and orange rice
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Season with salt and pepper. Place rice in a 12 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over rice.
Arrange browned chops on rice.
Pour chicken soup or bouillon cubes and water over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet. Set sausage aside.

title: creamy ham of broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine and add onion.
Saute until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, then gradually stir in milk.
Cook until smooth and creamy.
Add drained broccoli, ham cubes and salt to taste.
Simmer until thickened.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: herb bread
directions: Mix together last five ingredients.
Have sliced loaf sitting in foil "boat;" place cheese slices between bread slices, pour mixture over top of bread.
Bake, uncovered, in foil boat at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ham loaf mixture
directions: Mix graham crackers and milk into ham loaf mixture.
Mix until it is mushy.
Put in loaf pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
The last 15 minutes of cooking time, combine the brown sugar, a little pineapple juice and mustard together until it is creamy.
(Add more pineapple juice to make creamy.)
Pour over top of ham loaf.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in thoroughly the egg, orange rind and nuts.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice.
Bake in a greased 5-cup ring mold in a slow oven (325°) about 45 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Ice with softened cream cheese. Decorate with slices of stuffed olives and serve with fruit salad.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onions and steak strips in skillet with margarine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: leftover turkey-beef, etc. dish
directions: Slice onions and brown in a little oil.
Add minced garlic or sprinkle with garlic powder.
Sprinkle flour over onions.
Mix well.
Add broth and stir to gravy consistency.
Slice leftover meat and add to onion/gravy mixture.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Put mixture in casserole dish and top with mashed potatoes mixed with shredded cheese.
Put shredded cheese on top and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Before removing from oven, brown under broiler for a minute or two.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook the fryer until tender. Remove skin and bones. Cut into bite size pieces and put in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix together well the Veg-All vegetables, mushroom soup, celery soup and onion soup and spread over chicken. Blend together the flour, milk and melted margarine. Let stand 5 minutes and pour on top of casserole. Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: willy cake
directions: Blend in order and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Pour oleo over and stir to coat. Mix evaporated milk and cheese soup together.
Beat eggs with fresh milk.
In a large bowl, mix macaroni and cheese together. Next, add all together and stir well.
Pour into crock-pot and cook for 3 hours on low.
Sprinkle reserved cheese on top.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop the popcorn in a large brown paper bag.
Add nuts. In a large bowl, add butter, sugar and molasses.
Place in a microwave and cook on High for 2 minutes.
Must be boiling.
If not, cook in 30 second increments until boiling.
Stir in soda. Stir well. Pour over popcorn.
Shake well.
Fold over top of bag and place in microwave on High for 1 minute. Take out and shake.
Do 3 times. Pour in a large bowl.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Makes two 10-inch pies.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add hot water with baking soda in it.
Add vanilla, mashed bananas, salt and sifted flour. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake about 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pound breasts flat between layers of waxed paper.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan in a flat dish. Dip breasts in olive oil and dredge through the cheese/crumb mixture.
Place breasts in flat baking dish (put a little olive oil or spray Pam in bottom).
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and place 1 tablespoon pesto and 1 to 2 tablespoons tomato sauce on top of each breast.
Cover each breast with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Place breasts under broiler until cheese is bubbly and all is heated through, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with angel hair pasta and pesto sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream
butter,	sugar and flour together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add corn syrup and vanilla.	Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked
pie
shell.
Bake 30 minutes (or until done) at 350°.

title: countryside potatoes
directions: Combine grated raw potatoes, milk, sour cream or yogurt, salt, chives and butter or margarine; mix.
Place in greased casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jean's muffins
directions: Put all dry ingredients together, stir and add wet ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: whole wheat batter rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the yeast in warm water.
When it is dissolved, add to it 1 cup flour, kelp, Italian herbs, oil, honey and molasses; beat well.
Stir in the rest of the flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover; let rise 30 minutes.
Punch dough down. Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Brush tops with melted butter if desired.

title: broccoli or cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli or cauliflower in small pieces, using the buds and stems.
add chopped onion, grated cheese and bacon.
Mix dressing ingredients and mix together with other ingredients. Serves 8.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Put chicken broth in large pot.
Add broccoli and onion (frozen broccoli can be used).
Bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are cooked.

title: marinade for bulgogi
directions: Mix all together.
Makes enough marinade for 1 1/2 to 2 pounds of beef.

title: crab chowder
directions: In large pot, put potatoes in small amount of water with salt. Cook until potatoes can be mashed with water.
Add all other ingredients, except crab meat and fresh milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: oven polenta
directions: Make polenta by cooking cornmeal in water; salt to taste. Grease a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Spoon cooked polenta into pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate to cool and set firm, about 1 hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine crumbs and spices in bowl.
Wash chicken and remove skin.
Dip chicken pieces in yogurt or milk and then roll in seasoned crumbs.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese tuna
directions: Place 1 can of noodles in the bottom of a buttered casserole. Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over noodles in casserole.
Top with other can of noodles.
Shave 1 tablespoon of margarine over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fiesta corn bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in cornmeal.
Add corn, milk, butter, baking soda and salt.
Place half of the mixture in well-greased casserole.
Place chilies over mixture.
Add remaining corn mixture and top with cheese.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two greased and floured 9-inch pie pans.
Do not bake in a crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpernickel and cheese
directions: Mix the cheese, onion and Miracle Whip together in small bowl. Spread on slices of party loaf.
Place slices on cookie sheet. Put under broiler until starts to brown.
Serve immediately.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter and saute onion. Add consomme, broth, and rice to onion mixture. Place in a 9x13 inch casserole dish. Add mushrooms to top. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix browned hamburger with soups and put into a casserole dish.
Add a layer of cheese slices.
Spread Tater Tots over the top and bake, covered, in a 325° to 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Uncover near end of baking time to brown top of casserole if desired.

title: 3-bean casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, bacon and onion until hamburger is done.
Add sugar and stir until melted. Add all remaining ingredients. Bake in large casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine raisins, walnuts and 1/4 cup flour; toss well to coat and set aside.
Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Combine 1 1/4 cups flour, soda, salt and spices.
Stir into creamed mixture; stir in oatmeal (dough will be stiff).
Stir in raisin mixture and vanilla.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Broil chicken until tender; remove chicken from broth and debone.
The remaining broth is for your dumplings.
Mix flour, egg yolks, shortening, milk, broth and 1 teaspoon salt together. Mixture will be like a dough.
Add additional water, if necessary. Add 1/2 stick of margarine to the remaining broth.
Roll out the dumplings in flour; cut in strips.
As you put the dumplings in the broth, pull them a little so that they won't be too thick. Add the deboned chicken.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yum, yum!

title: meat miniatures
directions: Brown the first 5 ingredients together in a frying pan.
Cut each roll triangle into thirds.
Put filling on roll and fold in. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff with sugar and baking powder. Add crackers and fold in gently.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve cold with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: chocolate nut candy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Drop from spoon on cookie sheet; let harden.
Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip cold candy in this and put back on cookie sheet.

title: viva la chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cut into large pieces.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch strips.
Mix soups, milk, onion and salsa.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons of water or chicken stock.
Place 1/2 tortilla strips on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with half the chicken and half the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with cheese. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Next day, bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour with about 3 tablespoons pineapple juice. Add pineapple chunks and cheese.
Mix well and spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Then pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna stuffed jumbo shells
directions: In bowl, combine mayonnaise and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Spoon into shells; cover and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in salt water, mash.
Add butter, sugar, salt, cinnamon, egg yolks, milk and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form and fold gently but thoroughly into mixture.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat to 375° and bake 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add next 6 ingredients and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish, coated with cooking spray.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits, then partially separate each biscuit.
Press 1 cube of cheese into each one and insert.
Roll into cornmeal.
Arrange around edge of hot meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown. Serves 6.

title: jelly muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking
powder, sugar and salt into a large bowl. Put
shortening
into
small
skillet
and	melt.
Cool slightly. Beat egg
until
smooth;
add milk, then add cooled shortening. Pour mixture into flour mixture.
Stir only until dry ingredients are
moistened.
Line
muffin tins with paper liners.
Fill half with
batter,
add	a
teaspoon
of jelly, finish covering with batter.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Spread beans on large plate or platter.
Mix avocados and lemon juice.
Spread over beans.
Blend taco seasoning with sour cream.
Spread over avocados.
Top with green onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Grate the zucchini into a bowl and drain thoroughly.
Stir in the eggs, 3 tablespoons flour, Parmesan cheese, chives, parsley, pinch of garlic powder, salt and pepper. If mixture looks too liquid, add the 1 tablespoon flour.
Drop batter in hot, oiled skillet as for small pancakes and cook until browned.

title: sour cream coconut layer cake
directions: Make 3 cake layers, following the directions from Duncan Hines butter cake mix. Mix sugar, coconut and sour cream together. Let filling set at least overnight in refrigerator before cooking cake layers. Place filling between layers and all around cake. Keep in refrigerator.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to make syrup.
Add 3 tablespoons peach jello to hot syrup to dissolve.
Cool syrup.
Arrange peaches in pie shell.
Pour over cooled syrup.
Cover with whipped topping.

title: cherry and pecan pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup pecans.
Fold in 4 ounces cherries.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Beat cream cheese and margarine in mixer bowl until light.
Add confectioners sugar and remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Fold in remaining cherries and 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread over cake.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Spread refried beans or bean dip in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish, followed by the next layer, avocado dip.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise and spread over beans and avocado mixture. Sprinkle on 1/2 of taco seasoning mix.
Mix chopped green onions and chopped tomatoes and spread over other layers.
Add to the mixture the sliced olives, followed with the shredded cheese; spread evenly over all layers along with the remaining taco seasoning mix.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars well.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Add oatmeal.
Mix flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend in cornflakes and coconut or chopped nuts. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple whipped cream cake
directions: Prepare Jiffy mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for only 10 minutes and cool.
Combine cream cheese, instant pudding and 2 cups milk and pineapple juice.
Spread over cooled cake. Drop well drained pineapple over cream cheese mixture.
Cover cake with whipped topping; garnish with nuts.
Chill and keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: dinner roll
directions: Mix well.
Put in large greased muffin tin.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: In a skillet cook hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain and combine with spaghetti and sauce in a large baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Stir in cubes of Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Mix cocoa with sugar and flour. Gradually add milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add a small amount to slightly beaten egg yolks.
Stir gradually into remaining hot mixture.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Cool.
Cover with meringue.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer.

title: chili con carne
directions: In kettle, brown ground beef until slightly browned. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and simmer at least 1/2 hour on top of stove.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: In large kettle, cook beef and onion.
Add water, vegetables and potatoes.
Cook to soften vegetables.
Add tomatoes and paste. Put in desired seasonings.
Simmer until all vegetables are done.

title: mint tea
directions: Wash mint well.
Place with water into large saucepan.
Bring slowly to a boil.
Turn off heat and cover.
Let steep about 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: cheese strata
directions: Mix eggs, salt, mustard and milk.
Grease casserole.
Put 1 layer of bread and 1 layer of cheese (3 times).
Pour egg mixture over and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Round casserole is recommended.) Serves 6.

title: 1 gram of fat french fries
directions: Note:
Four sticks/slices per serving = 1 gram fat.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil the 3 to 4 potatoes in their own jackets.
Cook until tender.
Cool and peel.
Mash with 1 stick butter.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and milk.
Put half of mixture in buttered dish.
Put large marshmallows over layer.
Push down into mixture.
Add the rest of mixture.
Put marshmallows over top and push down.
Put corn flake crumbs, ground faint, in food chopper. Add 1/4 cup brown sugar and sprinkle on top with butter.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: superior french dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients (except oil and garlic) until blended, then add oil gradually.
Put in jar with garlic.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Beat egg.
Add cooking oil and beat thoroughly.
Add vinegar, salt and other seasonings.
Baste chickens about every 5 minutes. Makes 10 halves.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix 2/3 carton Cool Whip with cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Pour into a regular prebaked or graham cracker crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: boiled dinner
directions: Cook pot roast of beef using 1 quart of water, large sliced onion, salt and pepper.
Boil slowly on low heat until meat is well done.
Remove meat and cook remaining vegetables in the broth, adding water to cover vegetables.
Boil until all vegetables are well done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken chow mein ala grindle
directions: In a hot skillet STIR-FRY the celery and onions, use a small amount of oil, stirring continuously on a high heat.
Then cover and simmer approximately 5 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and separate broccoli into bite size pieces.
Cook bacon until crisp and crumble it. Chop onion, grate cheese and toss together.
Add dressing and let stand before serving.
Toss again, then serve.

title: oven corn to freeze
directions: Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir after first 15 minutes.
Cool. Put in bag for freezer.

title: chicken in the blanket
directions: Cook chicken.
Roll chicken and cheese in crescent.
Cook crescent as directed.
Serve hot with mustard.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place margarine in medium size casserole dish and melt.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Mix together broccoli, egg, soup, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and 1/2 of crackers.
Pour melted margarine over mixture; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, or until crackers brown well.

title: french silk pie
directions: Beat butter until very fluffy.
Add sugar; beat very well. Add vanilla and chocolate; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat about 3 minutes after each addition.
Add nuts.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill several hours before serving.
Very rich pie.

title: breakfast before
directions: Spray 9 x 12-inch casserole dish with vegetable cooking spray. Lay slices of bread in bottom.
Spread crumbled sausage over bread. Beat eggs, mustard, milk and mushroom soup until well mixed.
Pour over sausage and bread.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat again.
Add butter, then Karo syrup, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans and bake in pie shell at 350° until pie is set.

title: zippy clam dip
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid (if necessary add milk to make 3 tablespoons).
Add to cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Cook meat and onions and season to taste. Drain. Mix cornbread and muffin mixes together according to packages. Add cheese and corn. Add ground beef. Put in a 9 x 12 casserole dish and bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: tangy tomato slices
directions: In a small bowl or a jar with tight-fitting lid, mix the first 9 ingredients.
Layer onion and tomatoes in a shallow glass dish. Pour the marinade over; cover and refrigerate for several hours. Yields 12 servings.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil 2 full minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining 3 ingredients.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain and mix all beas.
Combine all other ingredients; mix well and add to beans; mix well.

title: cocoa spice drops
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, egg, margarine and vanilla until blended.
Combine dry ingredients. Add to egg mixture. Beat well. Beat an additional 1 minute at high speed. Stir in raisins.
Cover and chill about 1 hour.

title: lasagne florentine
directions: Set water for lasagne to boil.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet and saute garlic.
Add thawed spinach and let steam over low heat, covered, until limp.
Add sprinkle of salt or soy sauce if desired.
Set aside.
Add remaining tablespoon oil in large skillet and saute onion, add squash and stir until slightly cooked.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Bring the sugar and water to a boil for 5 minutes.
Soften the gelatin in the cold milk; stir until dissolved.
Add the scalded milk to the gelatin mixture to dissolve.
Add the sugar syrup, salt, eggs, vanilla, half and half and milk.
Pour into a 1-gallon ice cream freezer.
Use chipped ice and approximately 3 cups rock salt.
Turn freezer until ice cream becomes stiff.

title: spicy beef cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to room temperature.
Shred beef into small pieces.
(Set aside small amount to roll ball in.)
Mix cheese, beef and onion until smooth.
Shape into balls or rolls. Roll in remaining beef.
Refrigerate.
Set out a little before serving.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Spread approximately 1/2 teaspoon peanut butter between 2 crackers; make as many as you want.
Put on cookie sheet.
Freeze 1/2 hour.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Dip each in chocolate after you bring them out of the freezer.
Place on wax paper.
Let stand until hard.

title: homemade hot cocoa mix
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and blend well.
Or mix in large sealed container. Shake well. Store in tightly covered container. Yields 3 1/2 cups (about fifteen 6 ounce servings).

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter bread; cut into pieces.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Place bread in casserole or souffle dish; pour mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Start with cold oven.
Do not preheat oven.
Cream margarine, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Separate and unroll breadsticks.
Place 3 pepperoni slices in single layer over one-half of each breadstick.

title: tangerine cranberry relish
directions: Squeeze the juice of 2 tangerines to measure 1/2 cup.
Peel remaining 3 tangerines, separate segments.
Cut each segment in half, removing seeds.
In a 3-quart saucepan bring cranberries, sugar and tangerine juice to a boil over high heat, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, until all cranberries pop.
Spoon cranberry mixture into bowl and stir in tangerine segments.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours. Makes 4 cups.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, enchilada sauce and olives.
Bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer for 15 minutes.
Cut 2 tortillas into quarters.
Crisp the quarters and the remaining 6 tortillas in the oil over medium heat.
Drain.
Set aside the quartered tortillas and break up the remaining 6.
Combine the cottage cheese, egg and cheese.
Spread 1/3 of the meat mixture in a shallow baking dish. Top with 1/2 of the cheese mixture, then 1/2 of the broken tortillas.
Repeat layers, ending with meat mixture.
Place quartered tortillas on top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into small, bite size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Simmer over kerosene stove at 465° for about 4 weeks.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Cream
margarine
and
cheese;
add
flour
and pepper. Press through a cookie press, using small star blade.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cut while hot and sprinkle with paprika.

title: "grandmas" popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to firm ball (245°).
Remove and pour over corn.
Stir well.
Mold balls as quickly as possible.

title: minestre fagioli
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the garlic, celery, carrot, onion, fennel, and prosciutto; cook until the vegetables begin to soften; about 4 minutes. Add the tomatoes, broth, beans, and tubetti; bring to a boil and cook until pasta is tender, about 8 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir in the parsley, basil, salt and pepper. Sprinkle with parmesan if desired.

title: coq de la paroise
directions: Dip each piece of chicken in rum, carefully rubbing each side in liquor.
Coat each piece in light honey.
Dredge lightly in flour.
Brown in butter.
Place chicken in buttered baking dish. Add brandy, wine and bay leaf.
Cook chicken until tender at 350°. Add sour cream.
Season to taste and heat.
Sprinkle top with chopped almonds just before serving.

title: cucumber sandwich filling
directions: Grate and drain cucumber.
Add to cream cheese that has been softened with a little mayonnaise.
Season to taste.
Mix coloring into all.
Be sure not to get mixture too green.

title: "cracker jack" caramel popcorn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except popped corn, into a medium pan. Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes.
Pour over popped corn in a large roasting pan.
Bake at 225° for 45 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times. Cool; break into small pieces as it cools.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: chicken with grapes
directions: Crush crackers; mix with seasonings.
Dip chicken in milk, then dredge or shake in crumb mixture.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: last minute lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Spray 13 x 9 pan with cooking spray. Spoon 1/3 of sauce on bottom of pan.
Arrange ravioli on top, scatter spinach over layer of ravioli.
Top with 1/2 c. cheese. Cover with another layer of ravioli.
Top with sauce and remaining cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 25 minutes.
Uncover, bake 5 - 10 minutes more or until bubbly.

title: jello easter eggs
directions: First mix milk, sugar and jello thoroughly.
Then add nuts and coconut.
Form into egg shapes and chill.
Melt milk chocolate in a double boiler and pour evenly over eggs.
Refrigerate to harden.

title: spicy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; set aside.
Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla
and eggs.
Mix well; add dry ingredients and pour in pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter corn flake cookies
directions: Barely bring to a boil the sugar and white syrup.
Add the peanut butter while still hot; beat until smooth.
Add the vanilla.
Stir in the corn flakes.
Add a little melted butter while mixing.
Put out by spoonfuls onto waxed paper; let cool.

title: traffic lights
directions: Spread all slices of bread with butter, then spread whole wheat slices with Thousand Island dressing.
Cover 1/3 of the area of whole wheat slices with lettuce, reserving a little.
Remove egg yolks from whites and arrange yolk slices over center area of bread, reserving a little.
Place 4 tomato slices over remaining area on bread.
Season with salt and pepper.
Using a small 3/4-inch plain or fluted rounded cookie cutter, cut out 6 holes from each slice of white bread. Place bread, buttered sides down, over filling and press together firmly.
Cut each sandwich neatly in half to form "traffic lights."
Chop the reserved lettuce and tomato and slice egg yolk; use to fill the relevant holes in sandwich.
Garnish with a few green onion flowers.
Makes 4.

title: mee maw never fail cookies
directions: Mix butter and margarine.
Add the following in order: sugar, brown sugar, eggs, sifted flour, baking powder, baking soda, vanilla and nuts.
Roll in wax paper; refrigerate for 24 hours. Slice and bake at 350° until set (10 to 15 minutes).

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix onion, spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix and water chestnuts together.
Slice off top half of uncut loaf.
Cut or tear out middle of bread and chop or tear into bite size pieces.
Fill bread hollow with dip.
Arrange bites of bread around bread bowl with dip.

title: veg-all beef casserole
directions: Cook the noodles until tender, about 15 minutes in 1 1/2-quarts boiling water to which 1 1/2 teaspoons salt has been added. Lightly brown the onions in butter.
Add the ground beef and cook slowly until brown.
This will take about 10 minutes.
Blend in the flour; add cooked noodles and Veg-All including the liquid.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: kentucky cherry salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and pie filling.
Fold into mixture pineapple, marshmallows, Cool Whip and pecans.

title: chili con queso
directions: Heat cheese, tomatoes, chilies and onions until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: lasagna
directions: Spoon sauce into bottom of pan, enough to lightly cover bottom.
Add a layer of noodles.
Then add sauce on noodles, enough to lightly cover noodles.
Then add cottage cheese, then Mozzarella cheese.
Add another layer of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let it set 1 hour.

title: holy smoke pie
directions: Let margarine soften to room temperature, then cut into flour. Add chopped nuts.
Mixture will be "crumbly".
Pat into a large baking dish or pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: applesauce gingerbread cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
In large bowl, measure all ingredients except confectioners sugar.
With mixer at low speed, beat until well blended.
Increase speed to high; beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 1 hour or until center comes clean on toothpick.
Top with confectioners sugar if you like.

title: face painting
directions: Mix shortening and cornstarch until there are no lumps.
If the mixture is too thick, add a few drops of water; if too thin, add 1/4 teaspoon shortening at a time.
Divide the mixture into different bowls for different paint colors.
Add food coloring to make the desired color.
This paint may be refrigerated in a sealed container for up to three days.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Sift and add flour and baking soda.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon before baking.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or less.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups water, then add beaten egg.
Mix remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon or put in muffin pan to bake.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: applesauce
directions: In a 2-quart deep casserole combine apples, apple juice and sugar.
Mix well.
Cover.
Microwave on Full power for 10 to 12 minutes or until apples are tender, stirring once.
Mash apples to desired consistency by hand or process in a food processor filled with a steel blade.
Makes 3 1/4 cups.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Spread chicken pieces in baking pan. In saucepan, melt butter and add chicken bouillon, lemon juice plus water, sesame seed, parsley, salt and pepper.
Season to taste.

title: maple sweetened wheat bran-fig muffins
directions: Mix and bake 16 minutes at 400°.
Test with toothpick.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Preheat skillet at 325°, uncovered.
Add butter and allow to melt.
Place chicken pieces into skillet and brown on both sides. Season with salt and pepper.
Remove chicken from skillet. Reduce heat to simmer and add rice.
Combine soup, water and bouillon.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over rice.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done.
Reduce heat to warm for serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all the vegetables together.
Combine all the other ingredients and pour over the vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add onion and saute.
Add broccoli and soup.
Mix with rice and Cheez Whiz.
Bake in greased baking dish at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put pumpkin into blender.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, salt, pumpkin pie spice and milk.
Mix well and pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 7 minutes and reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes longer or until done.

title: chocolate chews
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat; stir in syrup and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, 2 cups powdered sugar and milk powder.
Mixture will be stiff.
Turn out onto surface dusted with confectioners sugar; knead 3 or 4 minutes or until stiff.
Divide into 4 pieces and roll into an 18-inch rope.
Cut into 3/4-inch pieces.
Wrap each in cellophane or waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss, cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put butter with crumbs to make crust in bottom of spring-form pan.
Soften cream cheese; add 1/3 cup sugar, 3 egg yolks and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well with electric mixer.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Heat all ingredients (except rice and sliced onions) until beef cubes melt.
Place rice in oven-safe casserole.
Add sliced onion, then pour liquid over.
Stir well.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered, then bake 45 minutes, covered, at 350°.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Stir all ingredients and mix together.	Bake at 150° to 200° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: To cook sweet potatoes, cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain, peel and put in a mixer bowl.
Add sugar, eggs, milk, salt, vanilla, margarine and raisins.
Beat with a mixer until smooth.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; then top with marshmallows and cook until they are melted and brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water; add lemon and pineapple juice.
Mix well; let cool.
Pour mixture into 2 large freezer bags and freeze.
Take out of freezer 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving.
Just before serving, add one ginger ale to each bag; mix well.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: quick ham casserole
directions: Add water to potatoes, onions and ham in skillet.
Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with Pam or oiled.
Add celery soup. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Add a tossed salad and have a meal.

title: fudgy pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; set aside.
Over low heat, melt butter; add cocoa and stir until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs and corn syrup; blend.
Stir in chopped nuts. Pour into shell.
Place pecan halves on top. Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cover, let stand about 8 hours before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape mixture into ball.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: lazy lady cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in a square baking dish. Mix milk, sugar and flour together.
Pour mixture into butter, then pour 2 cups fruit into center of dish.
Do not stir.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: lemon dainty
directions: Combine margarine, salt, sugar, flour
and mix well.
Add egg yolks, milk, lemon juice and rind.
Beat with rotary egg beater until smooth fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased baking dish. Set in pan of water.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry angel cake
directions: Make angel cake mix; cool cake.
Dissolve the jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add the frozen berries or fresh berries.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in 1 cup whipped cream; chill until firm. Cut cake into 3 layers.
Fill with strawberry mixture.
Put back in tube pan.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Add the confectioners sugar to cup of whipped cream; ice cake with mixture.
Top with fresh strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease pan with 1 Tbsp. butter. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Place frozen rolls on top of nuts. Sprinkle dry butterscotch pudding on top.

title: chicken
directions: Oil or butter casserole dish.
Put in raw chicken.
Cover with soups.
Add the 1/4 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours (covered).

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil ingredients, except popcorn, together until it forms a hard ball stage in cold water.
Pour over popcorn.
Form into balls.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 c. confectioners sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg in small bowl. Set aside. Combine milk, water, oil and lemon peel in medium saucepan. Heat to rolling boil over medium high heat. Add flour mixture all at once. Beat with wooden spoon until mixture pulls away from sides of pan into a ball. Remove from heat; cool slightly. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Heat 2 to 3 inches of oil in deep fryer or large saucepan to 350°.

Drop dough by tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Fry 3 or 4 puffs at a time, 4 to 6 minutes, or until golden brown, turning over several times. Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Makes 32 puffs.

title: classic green bean bake
directions: Combine undiluted soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Stir in green beans and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350 degrees 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: sorority punch
directions: Mix in blender the frozen strawberries, orange juice, bananas and crushed pineapple.
Place in punch bowl and add cold pineapple juice and cold 7-Up, approximately 32 ounces.
Mix and serve.

title: sunflower crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Crush corn flakes.
There should be about 3/4 cup. Blend in flour, salt and 1/4 cup cornflake crumbs.
(Reserve remaining 1/2 cup crumbs.)
Stir in sunflower nuts.
Chill dough thoroughly.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Scald first 3 ingredients together and let cool.
Mix all ingredients, should be a little sticky.
Let rise (I mix at night and let rise in cold oven overnight).
Divide dough in thirds. Roll out dough in rectangle.
Spread with melted butter; sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Roll jelly roll fashion. Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in loaf pans that have melted butter, brown sugar, raisins and nuts on bottom.
Let rise again until double.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, vanilla and salt; mix well. Slowly stir into eggs. Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a fork is slid in and comes out clean.

title: lemon lush or chocolate lush
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: greg's specialty pot roast
directions: Wash and cut pot roast into chunks.
Emerge into 4 quarts of hot tap water in a large pot.
Put on high heat.
Add salt, pepper, tenderizer, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.

Slice and add carrots, chopped onions, cubed potatoes and sliced bell peppers. Let cook on high heat for one (1) hour, add mushrooms, continue to cook on high heat until roast chunks are good and tender.
Add flour for gravy, let thicken and brown in pot, let simmer. Approximate cooking time, two (2) hours.
Approximately 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese and olive balls
directions: Mix cheese, flour and butter to make a dough.
Break off small pieces and flatten in hand.
Wrap olive in dough and place on baking sheet.
Bake until golden brown in 375° to 400° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: deer chili
directions: Start ground meat for a few minutes, then add deer meat.
Cook until gray, then add spices to meat and let cook into meat.
Drain off some grease, if any.
Add tomato sauce and 2 cans of water. Let simmer about 1 hour or so.

title: cheese-ham ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature in a small mixer bowl. Combine half of the cream cheese and all of the American cheese; beat with electric mixer until blended.
Beat in deviled ham, stir in pimento and onion.
Chill mixture for 2 or 3 hours.
Shape into a ball on a serving plate.
Combine remaining cream cheese and the milk; beat smooth.
Spread over ham mixture; chill well.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley, if desired.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Saute sausage and onion in just a little oil.
Add flour, milk, cream, thyme, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Add sauerkraut and lemon juice.
Heat through.
Serve immediately. Garnish with dill if desired.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti noodles. Let cool, mix all other ingredients together. Store in refrigerator, will keep for several days. Serves a large crowd.

title: aunt mary jane's corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until light brown.

title: biscuit dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in a gallon pot until well done.
Remove chicken from pot.
When cool, remove chicken, cut into pieces and put back in broth.
Put stick of butter in.
Add bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil, then take biscuits and cut each one into 4 pieces.
Drop into boiling broth. When dumplings are done, add cream of chicken soup.
Stir well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Spoon fruit filling over mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: peppermint candy canes
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and cream of tartar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook, stirring, to very hard ball stage (265°).
Remove from heat and add peppermint extract.
Divide in 1 portion; add food coloring to 1 part.
Pour out on greased platters.
When cool enough to handle, pull each part separately. Form in ropes and twist red part around white.
Cut in 8-inch lengths and form in the shape of candy canes.
Makes 10 canes.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients over medium heat until firm but not hard. Knead thoroughly and divide into fourths.
Add food coloring to make four colors.
Store in Ziploc bags.

title: grandma's taters
directions: Mix together in a casserole dish and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: baked chicken with provolone
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Place chicken in pan. Combine soup and wine and pour over chicken.
Cover loosely with foil and bake in oven at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove chicken from oven; top each piece with a slice of cheese.
Put back in oven without the foil and bake another 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: strawberry mousse parfait
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup water in small saucepan.
Let stand 1 minute.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and cook over medium heat until gelatin and sugar dissolve, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: no peek chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine uncooked rice, condensed cream of celery soup and onion soup mix blended with water.
Arrange chicken on soup mixture.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until chicken is tender and rice is done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar; cream and add egg yolks (well beaten).
Dredge in flour the broken pecans, cut candied cherries and cut pineapple; add to mixture.
Add lemon extract.
Add 4 1/2 cups flour (sifted) with 1 teaspoon baking powder sifted in. Lastly, add 6 egg whites (well beaten).
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in a large angel cake pan (well-greased and floured).
Place in a 250° oven and bake for 5 hours, with pan of hot water above and below cake pan.
This cake will keep indefinitely.

title: reindeer droppings
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Make into balls.
Dip into coating.

title: lemon squares or bars
directions: Mix together butter, flour and confectioners sugar and spread into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oven fried zucchini spears
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
On shallow plate, combine all ingredients except zucchini and oil; set aside.
Slice off ends of zucchini.
Cut each lengthwise into quarters, then each quarter into half.

title: erin's party mix
directions: You use Bugles, square cereal, a little bit of round cereal, peanuts and some raisins.
Put some kind of sauce on it.
I don't know what kind.
It's real thin.
Then you have to cook it for 5 minutes on 5°.
Take it out and eat it.
It's not hot, because the sauce kind of cools it.
It's
kind of a hot party mix.
Put it in the middle of the table and whatever you want, you pick it out.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Scald milk
and add sugar and salt in right away (helps cool milk).
In a large glass, combine yeast, water and sugar. Let set 5 minutes at least.

title: baked catfish fillets
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt, pepper and lemon pepper.
Coat each fillet and place on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, turning once.

title: doughnut cupcakes
directions: Mix all preceding ingredients.
Bake in muffin tins filled half full for 25 minutes at 350°.
After baking, melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine.
Dip cupcake tops in melted butter.
Coat with mixture made of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, brown sugar and chopped pecans.
Set aside.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Butter Bundt pan well.
Dip rolls in melted butter; roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture and place in pan.
Pour rest of butter over rolls. Sprinkle pudding mixture over top.
Leave in warm place overnight, lightly covered.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Set pan in the oven overnight to rise.

title: potato soup(crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot except for half and half and simmer on low, for about 6 to 8 hours.
I start this before I go to work in the morning.
About 1/2 hour before serving, add half and half.

title: pepperoni loaf
directions: Defrost dough on countertop overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°. Roll out dough on cookie sheet.
Open oven and place on oven door to rise for 15 to 20 minutes or until puffy.
Return to countertop and cover with cheese slices.
Next, cover cheese with pepperoni slices.
Roll up dough like you would a jelly roll.
Turn open side down and pinch ends to close.
Baste with egg white, then sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve slices plain or with your favorite tomato sauce.

title: cornbread fritters
