directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Heat oil in skillet and add batter to form pancakes.
Cook until golden brown and slightly firm.
Good with fresh vegetables and dried beans.

title: raspberry peach smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Cover and process until smooth. Serve immediately in tall glasses. Garnish with fresh mint, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: apple compote
directions: Boil sugar and water to syrup.
Add sliced lemon.
While lemon is cooking, core, peel and quarter apples.
Add apples to syrup and cook until tender.
Good either hot or cold.

title: spanish meat dish
directions: Mix all together and pack in a loaf tin or ring mold.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugars.
Add eggs.
Stir in flour and soda; add vanilla.
Roll into small slender rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Put into freezer.
When ready to cook, slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: rainbow frozen dessert
directions: Cut or tear cake into small pieces; divide in thirds. Sprinkle strawberry gelatin over one, lime gelatin over one and orange gelatin over one.
Toss each lightly to coat cake with gelatin.
In 10-inch tube pan, put strawberry cake pieces in bottom; spoon strawberries over.
Spread 1/3 of ice cream over. Repeat layers with lime cake pieces, blueberries, ice cream, orange cake pieces, mandarin oranges and ice cream.
Freeze until firm.
Unmold on a chilled dessert plate.
Makes 16 servings.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Put broth and chicken together.
Thicken with flour.
Add cream cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
Pour in baking dish with cooked pot pie bows.
Top with buttered bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (covered).

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, flour, and soda. Add vanilla, bananas, and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350 in 9 x 13 inch pan for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Frost when cool.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package.
Cool completely.
Using wooden spoon handle, poke random holes in cake top.
Pour pina colada drink mixer over top of cake, filling holes.
Spread pineapple over cake top, covering completely.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: apricot-almond bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Beat egg until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and oil; mix well.
Blend flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add flour mixture alternately with orange juice and water.
Stir in apricots and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Slice the bread in half lengthwise.
Brush each half with flavored olive oil.
Top each with grated cheese.
Place each half on broiler pan.
Broil until golden brown.
Slice into servings.

title: 14 layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Alternate adding flour and milk while beating at a low speed. Add vanilla last.
Put a big spoon (commercial type) of batter in iron griddle.
Cook only a few minutes at 450°.
Do not turn or flip until done, then flip right side up to cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in 450° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.
Add more cayenne pepper if you prefer your cornbread hot.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Scramble 2 dozen eggs, 1/4 pound butter and 1/4 milk.
Combine 2 cans cream of mushroom soup, wine and chilies together in separate bowl. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan, scrambled eggs, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scrambled cabbage
directions: Place salad oil in skillet.
Heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook 5 minutes, no longer.
Stir once while cooking. Makes 6 servings.

title: southwest turkey salad
directions: Combine salsa, cumin, salt, pepper and sour cream. Refrigerate. Rinse and drain beans. Add corn and drain. Combine turkey, celery, beans and corn. Place on shredded lettuce. Top with turkey mixture. Serve with tortilla chips and dressing on the side.

title: cheesy chicken pot pie
directions: In a saucepan combine soup, 1/2 cup milk, onion, celery, carrots, cream cheese, Parmesan cheese and salt.
Cook and stir until the cream cheese is melted.
Stir in chicken and broccoli. Heat through.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
In a medium bowl, combine the egg, oil, pancake mix and cheese.
Spoon over hot chicken
mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil and drain squash.
Mix all other ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: molasses pie
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and sugar for crumbs.
Mix together molasses, boiling water and soda for pie mixture. Sprinkle half of the crumbs in bottom of 2 pie shells.
Pour half of pie mixture in each pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over the pie mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top crumbs are brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on low all night.
Cover with cloth instead of glass top while cooking.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain grease off.
Cook noodles and drain.
In a medium size baking dish, layer noodles first, then add a layer of hamburger.
Dilute soup (1/2 soup and 1/2 water) and pour over noodles and hamburger.
Sprinkle cheese over that, then top with 1/2 can of onions.
Repeat the same way again and end up with onions on top.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until cheese melts and starts to turn brown.

title: chocolate chess pie 2
directions: Melt butter and chocolate. Blend flour in white sugar.
Add milk, vanilla and brown sugar.
Stir well.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and salt; set aside. In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter, oil and sugar. Beat with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition. Stir in zucchini. Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and walnuts. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool before frosting.

title: grandma's sliced cucumbers
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar or bowl.
Stir well.
Place in refrigerator; wait one week; shake daily.
This will keep up to 6 months in refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam cooking spray.
Make both puddings and let stand a few minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts. Set aside.
Beat eggs lightly; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients; stir only until moist.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: egg pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, eggs, milk and nutmeg together.
Batter will be lumpy.
Melt butter in a large frying pan.
(I find that an iron frying pan works well).

Add batter. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until pancake is nicely brown and puffy. Remove from pan to warm plate and spread with a couple tablespoons of lingonberries; sprinkle with lemon or lime juice over the berries and sprinkle the whole pancake with powdered sugar.
Eat! You will think you died and went to heaven!

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and allow to sit at least 2 hours refrigerated.

title: classic raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, brown sugar, sugar, milk, egg and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; add to mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes; cool on wine rack.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour. Chill several hours.

title: quick orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Use ice cream freezer or freeze in home refrigerator-freezer.
If freezing in home freezer, stir after about 1 hour and again in about 2 more hours. Will make sherbet be more creamy.

title: whatniks
directions: Preheat oven to 275° and grease cookie sheets.
Sift together brown sugar, flour and salt.
Fold in egg white, vanilla and then pecans.
Drop by small rounds on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Place all ingredients, except cheese, into mixing bowl and beat with a whisk until emulsified.
Cut or break cheese into small chunks of varying size.
Add to emulsion and combine thoroughly. Store, refrigerated, in glass or plastic container. Yields about 1 3/4 to 2 cups.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Mix thoroughly the cornmeal, flour and salt, then add balance of ingredients without mixing.
Grease muffin pans or cornstick pans well and heat.
Stir mixture thoroughly and pour into the hot pan.
Bake at 450° until done.
The bread will be moist and brown on the bottom.

title: marinade for flank steak
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into large plastic baggie that seals.
Put flank steak into mixture.
Seal and marinate in the refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours.
Turn several times.
Cook on grill to desired doneness.

title: our favorite baked beans
directions: Cut bacon up into 1/4 to 3/4-inch.
Fry and add to beans with drippings.
Cut onion up and fry until tender.
Mix all together. Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: magically moist chicken
directions: Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Place bread crumbs in large plastic bag.
Add chicken, one piece at a time.
Shake to coat well.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Bake in 425° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese and egg brunch
directions: Place half of the bread cubes in a buttered 3-quart casserole. Layer with mushrooms, olives and cheeses.
Top with remaining bread cubes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Put in greased and floured bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on box.
Drain and add cheese, mayonnaise, eggs, soup and onion.
Combine well and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peppers in oil
directions: Clean and boil peppers for 5 minutes; drain.
Add oil, sugar and ketchup.
Bring to a boil; seal in jars.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomatoes and lettuce.
Hollow out tomatoes and spoon tuna salad inside.
Sit tuna tomato on bed of lettuce. Chill and serve.

title: zucchini puffs
directions: Slice zucchini in 36 (1/4-inch) rounds.
In small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Spread each zucchini slice with a thin layer of mayonnaise mixture and place in broiler pan. Broil 5-inches from heat in preheated broiler 30 to 60 seconds or until top is golden brown.
Each round is about 20 calories.

title: mounds
directions: Mix all the above together and pat into a large pan.
Put in the refrigerator.
Then cut into 1 inch squares.
Dip in 2 bags of chocolate chips, melted in 1 block paraffin.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until just tender; don't cook too long.
Drain. Add butter and stir well.
Add cheese and add milk, 1/2 cup at a time.
Keep macaroni on simmer until all cheese is melted.
Keep adding milk until it has a creamy texture, not lumpy.
Enjoy.

title: mock raspberry jam
directions: Core tomatoes and cut into chunks.
Process in blender until you have 2 cups.
Boil 2 cups blended tomatoes with 2 cups sugar for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add powdered gelatin.
Pour into clean containers and refrigerate or freeze.
Makes 2 pints.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl combine egg and 1/4 cup of the soup.
Stir in hot rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 20 small balls; place in a 10-inch skillet.
Mix remaining soup with Worcestershire sauce and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to boil, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir often.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: south african lazy chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in casserole dish. Mix mayonnaise, jam and onion soup together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large crock-pot and heat on low for three hours.
Serve hot.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Slice lemons very thin with rind on.
Mix with sugar and let stand overnight.
Blend occasionally.
Add eggs to lemon mixture and mix.
Put in shell, arranging slices evenly.
Cover with top crust.
Cut several slits near center.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Bake for 20 minutes more or until knife comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: wild rice dressing
directions: Combine wild rice, chicken broth, white wine and 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 45 minutes.
In large skillet, melt 6 tablespoons butter and add pecans.
Saute until brown (3 to 4 minutes).
Add ham, apples and cinnamon.
Continue to saute until apples are almost cooked (about 5 minutes).
Add liqueur, salt and pepper and cook 3 more minutes.
Set aside.
Add pecan rice to wild rice mixture and cook 20 minutes more.
Add ham, pecan, apple mixture to rice and blend.

title: cocoa bundt cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 12-inch Bundt pan.
In large mixer bowl, blend flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat on low speed 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Drizzle with chocolate glaze.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: canned okra
directions: Cover okra with water.
Add vinegar and salt.
Cook until okra changes color and pack in clean hot jars.

title: easy pork parmigiana
directions: Combine egg and water.
Set mixture aside.
Combine Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoned bread crumbs and set aside.
Place each piece of pork between two sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet.
Dip pork in egg mixture and dredge in crumb mixture.
Cook pork slices in vegetable oil over medium heat until browned.
Arrange pork slices in lightly greased 8-inch baking dish.
Top with spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 5 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Remove bone from chicken, break into bite size pieces.
Layer in large deep casserole dish.
Heat soups, milk and seasoning (salt and pepper to taste) until well blended and pour over chicken.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake rolls flat.
Punch holes with fork; roll so rolls will not raise too thick.
Bake until golden brown; cool.
Mix the cream cheese, soup mix, dressing mix and sour cream until well blended.
Spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle vegetables and cheese on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cut into squares.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Add last 5 ingredients to bowl and mix. Pour batter into 2 greased and floured bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: meat ball stroganoff
directions: In a large bowl, combine beef with 2 tablespoons of soup mix and milk; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch meat balls.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Brown meat balls; remove pan from heat.
Stir in flour, remaining soup mix, water and parsley flakes.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Gradually stir in sour cream until thoroughly blended.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together.
Add sugars and continue to beat.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy. Sift flour; measure and add salt, soda and baking powder.
Sift again.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into balls 1-inch in diameter.
Place balls 2 to 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Press flat with fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: party sandwiches(tuna filling)
directions: Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix and
let stand overnight.
When ready to serve, mix enough mayonnaise or salad dressing to cover salad.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix the flour and sugar in large bowl.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar the margarine, water, oil and cocoa. Add and mix well the eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, baking soda and buttermilk.
Pour on sheet cake pan with bottom and sides greased and floured.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tuna taylor salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the tuna, cheese, celery, onion, mayonnaise, sour cream and pepper. Spread on the bread and serve at once. Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: cheesy burger and green chile rice
directions: Combine broth and onion in medium skillet; bring to boil, add instant rice. Cover and turn off heat. Let stand for 5 minutes. Add Welsh Rarebit, chiles, beef, tomatoes and ketchup. Cook over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes until hot and thickened. Add salt and ground black pepper to taste.

title: basic dough
directions: Dissolve yeast, salt and sugar in 2 cups warm water.
Pour oil over flour and add water solution, mixing well.
Knead until dough is blended.
Let dough stand until it rises.
Form dough into little balls and let them set about 20 minutes.
Dough is now ready to be patted or rolled.
Dough may be made in smaller amounts.
Dough may be frozen until needed.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in rice and salt.
Cover and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 30 minutes.
Add milk and boil gently, stirring occasionally until mixture thickens slightly, about 5 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in a bowl. Gradually stir in rice mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and sprinkle spices over top.
Place casserole in a pan of water about 1 inch deep.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
You'll love it!!!!

title: pie crust
directions: Step 1:
Bake Duncan Hines sour cream cake according to directions in oblong pan.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar; cut in butter.
Pat in to 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting into bars.

title: candied carrots
directions: Mix all in saucepan.
Boil until liquid becomes syrupy.

title: carl's duck farm dip
directions: Grind onions, garlic, peppers, pickles and olives.
Add cottage cheese, mayonnaise, ketchup and seasonings.
Mix well. Let stand for at least 2 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: sunshine potato balls
directions: Beat butter, milk, sugar, salt and pepper into potatoes.
Form 2-inch balls with marshmallow centers; roll in corn flakes.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
These can be frozen ahead and baked directly from freezer for 45 minutes.
Makes 18 to 20 potato balls.

title: any fruit coffee cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine choice of fruit and 1/4 cup water. Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes. Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch; stir into fruit mixture. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 more minutes.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, stir together 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut in 4 tablespoons margarine or butter until mixture looks like fine crumbs.
Combine egg, buttermilk and vanilla; add to flour mixture.
Stir until just moistened.
Spread 1/2 of batter into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread fruit mixture over batter.
Drop remaining batter in small amounts on top of filling.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup flour; cut in remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: great apple cake
directions: Batter will be thick.
Mix together thoroughly eggs, sugar and oil.
Then add soda, salt, vanilla, cinnamon and flour, mixing again.
Add apples and nuts; mix well.

title: fudgy chocolate ice cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat chocolate, milk, egg, and vanilla. Stir in half and half, whipping cream and nuts. Put in ice cream freezer container and freeze.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until well blended. Marinate vegetables overnight.
This recipe is enough for vegetables packed into a lettuce keeper.

title: baked fried chicken
directions: Combine oil and seasonings.
With a pastry brush, rub mixture well into each piece of chicken.
Place layer deep in shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in hot oven at 400° for 20 minutes. Turn pieces and continue baking for 40 minutes longer or until tender.

title: nonfat cream corn
directions: Cook in crock-pot 4 hours on low.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: vanilla layer cake with chocolate-ginger frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray cake pans with nonstick cooking spray.

In small bowl, combine cake flour, baking soda and salt. In medium bowl with mixer on high speed, cream sugar and margarine; add egg and 2 teaspoons of vanilla extract, beating until smooth. Gradually beat in flour mixture alternately with milk, until batter is smooth.
Evenly divide batter between prepared pans; bake 15 to 20 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cakes cool in pans 5 minutes; remove cakes from pans and set on racks to cool.
Transfer 1 cake to serving platter; set aside. Cover.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pack into 2 buttered loaf pans. Bake for 30 minutes in a 300° oven. Cool and refrigerate.
Slice.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and brown sugar.
Add peanut butter.
Add soda, vanilla, salt, flour and oats.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over beef.
Bake at 350° until meat is tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: alaska sourdough pancakes
directions: The night before the pancakes are wanted, mix well in a medium size glass bowl the warm water, yeast and flour.
Cover and place in a warm place or a closed cupboard overnight.

title: quiche
directions: Mix oleo, Bisquick, eggs and milk in blender or with egg beater.
Add cheese, onion and green pepper.
Add ham and pour into greased casserole.
This makes its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sparkling orange sipper
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and combine.
Pour over tall glass of ice and serve.

title: sandy's buttermilk corn bread
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Beat egg in smaller bowl and whisk in butter slowly, until mixed well.
Whisk in buttermilk.

title: microwave baked onions
directions: Peel onions and cut in sections.
Place in microwavable dish. Sprinkle
with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Add a few granules of bouillon in center of onions and top with a pat of margarine. Cover and cook until tender.
Delicious!

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: In large bowl combine
condensed milk and cold water.
Add pudding and mix well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Layer pudding mix, bananas and wafers into a 2 1/2 qt. bowl until all mixture is gone finishing with pudding mix.
Chill.
Awsome!!! Serves 12.

title: spanish rice
directions: In heavy skillet, heat cooking oil until hot.
Add rice and stir until browned.
Add ground beef and cook until red is gone and meat is almost done.
Add onions and peppers and saute for a few minutes.
Add tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough water to keep it from sticking as it cooks.
Cook until rice is done.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Mix together and cook in a crock-pot on high 3 to 4 hours.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage very fine.
Cut bell pepper, celery and carrot into small pieces.
Dice onion.
Mix all ingredients together. You can add more Miracle Whip as desired.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine drained beans, green pepper, celery and pimento.
Add 1/2 chopped onion, if desired.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour this over bean mixture.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, stirring 3 or 4 times.
Drain before serving.

title: potato and salami casserole with cheese
directions: Melt
butter in small saucepan over medium heat.
Blend in flour,
salt
and pepper.
Add milk slowly.
Cook and stir until smooth
and
thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the cheese. Arrange
half
of
the
potatoes in a greased 3 quart casserole dish.
Add a layer of eggs, then a layer of salami. Cover with about
half of the cheese sauce.
Repeat layering. Bake in moderate
oven
at
350° for about 20 minutes or until browned and bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti squash stir fry
directions: Saute pepper, onion and garlic in olive oil, about 3 minutes until tender.
Add tomato, zucchini, mushrooms, vinegar and seasonings.
Add squash.
Toss well and sprinkle almonds.
Serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken on bottom of well-greased 9 x 12-inch casserole. Layer next 5 ingredients.
Mix soups, sour cream, sherry, salt and pepper and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with poppy seed.
Drizzle melted butter over crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
May be prepared a day ahead or even frozen to use when needed.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressings and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve with freshly ground black pepper if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick green beans
directions: Stir flour, salt and pepper into butter; add 1 cup milk and cook until thickened.
Pour over beans.
Sprinkle cheese over top and brown under broiler.

title: chicken almond spread
directions: Combine all ingredients to spreading consistency.
Spread on potato chips and garnish with paprika.
Broil until lightly brown. Serve immediately.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
In casserole dish, combine macaroni and cheese, corn and tuna.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for about 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp; crush.
Mix all ingredients, except half and half.
Then add half and half to desired consistency.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter and cream cheese together.
Add flour and sugar together.
Add the eggs.
Mix on low speed until blended well.
Cook at 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: philadelphia cream cheese cake
directions: Cream the butter and cheese together. Add sugar; blend well. Add eggs alternating with flour.
Beat well after each addition. Pour mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Glaze while hot with sour cream frosting.
tags: Betty Crocker vanilla sour cream frosting

title: cabbage surprise
directions: Cut up all ingredients into bite size pieces. Place all ingredients in colander.
Rinse clean with cold water.
Let them sit until completely drained.
In a skillet, melt butter.
Place all ingredients into skillet and cook for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 24 minutes.
Cut into pieces, about 2 x 1-inch. Yields 4 dozen appetizers.

title: company broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package (let water cook low). Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion and eggs.
Melt stick of margarine; pour over crackers.
Stir and put on top of dish. Combine soup, mayonnaise and cheese in small saucepan over low heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Pour soup over all; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla before last flour. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan, 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Does not need icing, but can ice.

title: picnic slaw
directions: Grate cabbages and carrot; chop onions.
Mix in bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in separate bowl and pour on salad. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cool whip and pineapple cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Follow cake mix instructions. Pour into large jelly roll pan (with sides).
Bake 20 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie(makes 2)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Combine ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Arrange pecans on top.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Quarter each biscuit.
Place 3/4 c. of sugar and cinnamon into a plastic bag.
Place quartered biscuits and mix to coat.
Place coated biscuits into a greased cake pan. Sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Place in bowl; mix while waffle iron is heating.
Cook and serve.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the flour, cornmeal, cornstarch, salt, paprika, oregano, sage and pepper.
In a shallow bowl, beat eggs and water.
Dip chicken in egg mixture; place in the bag, a few pieces at a time, and shake until coated. In an electric skillet, heat 1-inch of oil to 375°.
Fry chicken, a few pieces at a time, for 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until golden and crispy.
Place in two ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pans.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: *Or use all Mozzarella if you like.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Soak bread in milk before adding. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, water, brown sugar, white vinegar and garlic powder in one bowl.
Spread wings in 9 x 13-inch pan; pour mix over wings.
Marinate at least 1 hour (better 6 hours).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn frequently so wings get brown all around.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Then add oleo and egg.
Mixture will be coarse.
Put 1/2 mixture on bottom of 7 1/2 x 12-inch pan. Cover with 1 can cherry pie filling.
Cover with last 1/2 of cake mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: fudge
directions: Over medium heat bring to boil sugar, milk and butter.
Boil for 4 minutes, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat and add chocolate and stir until dissolved.
Add Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into pans.
Drop pan on table to get air out.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook 18 to 24 hours in a crock-pot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain in large mixing bowl.
Add next 4 ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs and mix well.
Place over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil, and nectar together.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice together.
Pour over cake while it is still hot to make a glaze.

title: mix and drop biscuits
directions: Mix; sift in flour to thicken.
Drop from spoon.
Bake at 350°.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat potatoes, sugar, butter, eggs, milk and vanilla until fluffy. Stir in the coconut.
Spoon into a 2-1/2 qt. baking dish.
Combine the brown sugar, flour, pecans and melted butter for topping until well blended and sprinkle over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: holiday fillet mignon
directions: Trim filets and wrap with bacon strips.
Saute in 5 tablespoons oleo; add 6 tablespoons of boiling water.
Bake until done!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place zucchini in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half of seasonings.
Layer tomatoes and onions.
Use remaining seasonings.
Top
with Parmesan and Cheddar cheeses.
Dot with margarine.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple-pecan spread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook meat in oil until brown.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until onion is well done.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt, chili powder and olives.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Roll out biscuit mix and place over mixture.
Slit holes in dough.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and sliced bread or dinner rolls.
Add some stock until well moistened.
Saute onions in 1 tablespoon margarine until softened.
Add onions to bread and stock and mix well, adding more stock as needed to keep well moist.
Grate 7 eggs and add to mixture.
Add more stock as needed.
Add chicken and mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and place some margarine pats around top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until browned.
Use leftover stock and 1 grated egg for gravy with 1 tablespoon flour mixed in cold water.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water; add blueberries, pineapple and salt.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch dish and chill until firm.

title: everybody's cake
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients in large kettle for 20 minutes, covered.
Set aside to cool.
Then add sifted flour, baking soda, honey and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
May be iced, powdered sugar, or plain for good eating.

title: raisin bran peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, white sugar and brown sugar together.
Add and mix well eggs and vanilla.
Then add flour, baking powder, salt, soda and Raisin Bran; mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Make 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheets (I use parchment paper) and flatten with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350° until lightly brown.
Slightly cool before removing from pan.
This is a good nourishing cookie.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Bake cake and let cool.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in a 4 1/2 to 5-quart dish.
Pour 1/4 cup of coffee over cake.
Then layer half of the pudding, Cool Whip and candy bars.
Then repeat the cake, coffee, etc. one more time.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Serve over cream cheese with crackers.
Keep in refrigerator. Will last a long time.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan.
Add onion; cook until tender, not brown.
Combine and mix flour, sugar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Stir into onion mixture.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, shrimp and olives.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.

title: elegant chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl combine chicken, celery, grapes and coconut. Chill.

title: southwest chili rellenos with sweet pepper and onion sauce(serves six)
directions: Saute celery, corn and garlic in oil in medium skillet 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken and cok 5 minutes; remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and chili seasoning.

title: bahas
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and add tomato sauce.
Add water to taco seasoning mix and add to hamburger with all other ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes and serve on french bread or buns.
If desired top with shredded cheese and place in oven just long enough to melt cheese.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Tie spices in bag and add to fruit juices.
Bring to a boil, then turn heat down and simmer slowly for a few minutes.
Remove spices before serving.
Serve hot.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peanut butter fluff
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil; reduce heat and boil 11 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat together and immediately pour into greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: beef shanks
directions: Place 3 shanks of beef on bottom of crock-pot.
Pour on soup mix and half of tomato sauce.
Place remaining shanks, rest of sauce and beef broth.
Cook slow all day, approximately 8 hours. Serves 6.

title: stuffed pizza
directions: Spread 1 ball of dough on round pizza pan.
Fry sausage, drain. Add mushrooms, onion, garlic, sauce and pepperoni.
Warm through. Place on pizza shell.
Top with cheeses.
Form 1/2 ball of dough and place on top.
Turn edges under.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When brown on top, remove from pan and bake on rack to brown bottom (5 to 10 minutes).
If your dough has holes on bottom this will create a mess.
Makes 8 big servings.

title: health salad
directions: Drain all the canned vegetables.
Place all ingredients in a large, covered container.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix according to normal pound cake mixing instructions.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan about 5 minutes before removing.
Complete the cooling on cake rack.
Frost as desired or leave plain.
Great either way.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash. Mix with other ingredients. Will keep a week in refrigerator or freezer.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Season chicken with garlic powder and brown.
Place into pot and add the rest of the ingredients.
Then simmer for about 30 minutes.
Then put
your
rice
on
to
cook.
You
can make whatever vegetable you want to stir-fry.

title: 8 vegetable salad
directions: Mix lima beans, peas and carrots together.
Cook until tender, but not soft.
Cool.
In a large bowl, mix with remaining vegetables.
Pour dressing over vegetables and toss gently.
Chill 2 hours or preferably overnight for more delicious flavor.
(If chilled overnight, add tomatoes at last tossing for crispness.) Toss again before serving.
This is a great "make ahead" salad for a group of 10 to 15.
Keeps well for 3 to 4 days in the refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients 3 times.
Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Mix dry ingredients into oil and sugar mixture, add eggs, pumpkin and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.
You can add raisins if you wish.
It makes 4 loaves of bread.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Place flour in bowl; stir in beer, salt and oil.
Blend thoroughly (there will be lumps).
Cover bowl and set in warm place for couple of hours.
Stir in egg yolk.
When ready to cook, beat egg white until stiff and fold in.
Dip fish and fry.
You can drink the other half of beer.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Shape into meat balls and brown.
Remove from pan.
Pour grease from pan.
Cook chili sauce and grape jelly until it blends, then add meat balls and simmer 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine baking powder and flour; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before turning out.

title: crab muffins
directions: Beat cheese spread and butter until creamy.
Add garlic powder, salt and mayonnaise and beat with beaters.
Add crabmeat with a fork.
Spread on half of six whole English muffins, then cut into quarters.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
If frozen, bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: house dressing
directions: Mix well and keep refrigerated.
Keeps well.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Work in butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Put through a cookie press.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cookies 'n cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
In large bowl, combine all cake ingredients, except crushed cookies at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Gently stir in the 1 cup crushed cookies.

title: catherine's cheese ball
directions: All ingredients should be room temperature. Mix together, then roll in nuts; chill overnight.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, and flour.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat and add cherries and gelatin.
Cool approximately 10 minutes and add bananas and pecans.
Fill pie shells.
Chill and top with whipped cream.
Serves 18-24.

title: fruit punch with strawberries
directions: Combine fruit juices and sugar.
Chill thoroughly.
Add ginger ale and strawberries just before serving.
Pour over cake of ice in punch bowl.
Float thin slices of lemon or lime.
Yields 65 servings.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, corn syrup and chocolate.
Boil 5 minutes or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add butter and stir until it starts to thicken, approximately 10 minutes.
Add vanilla. Stir 5 minutes, then add nuts.
Spread mixture in a greased pan (butter or margarine); cut into squares when hard.
Stir constantly.

title: coconut pecan bundt cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, water, oil, pudding mix and sour cream together really well.
Then stir in icing.
Cook in greased and floured bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Save a few mandarin oranges to garnish top.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix juices and Kool-Aid according to directions.
Add bananas and chill.
Add chilled ginger ale before serving.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and use or serve.
Refrigerate remainders.

title: salmon cheese loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pack into a loaf pan.
Cover the top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter.
Add flour and chill.
Make balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes about 50.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Combine margarine and sugar; add bread and pineapple.
Add eggs.
Mix together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix with broth and stuffing.
Place half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken, mayonnaise and onion and spread on top of stuffing in pan.
Put remaining stuffing on top. Beat eggs and milk together and pour over casserole.
Spread soups on top.
Chill.
(Great for making ahead!)
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: green chilies enchiladas with beef
directions: Heat soup, Velveeta and milk in top of double boiler until melted; add green chilies.
Drain grease from browned meat. Combine grated Longhorn cheese, onions and browned meat.
Dip each tortilla in hot oil briefly to soften. (Do not allow them to fry). Drain well.
Fill tortillas with meat mixture, roll together tightly and place in baking dish.
Pour Velveeta sauce over top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine together:
kraut, onion, green pepper, celery and pimento.
Sprinkle sugar over salad.
Add vinegar and oil.
Toss to combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain off excess juice before serving.

title: garlic bread
directions: Melt butter or margarine and garlic salt to boiling.
Put foil on bottom of pan and dip one side of each piece of sliced bread in butter mixture.
Place loaf together again on top of foil.
Put foil on top and bake at 275° for 40 minutes, then slit the top foil and bake at 275° for 1 hour and 20 minutes longer (2 hours total).

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Add vanilla; beat until blended.
Makes 3 cups.
Optional: Stir in 3/4 cup pecans.
Add mashed bananas or strawberries. Sprinkle 1/4 cup pecans on top of cake after frosting.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Bake beef slowly at 350° until done (use a small amount of water). Remove any fat and cut in bite size pieces.
Add all other ingredients and cook about 1/2 hour, until all is well blended. Refrigerate or freeze in small portions.

title: baked mexican salad
directions: Spread ground beef in bottom of a deep casserole.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: indian corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon and drain well.
Saute onion.
Cook potatoes with just enough water to cover, about 10 minutes, until tender. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thickened.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough 1 hour.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Line 14-inch pizza pan with foil.
Overlap cookie slices and bake at 375° 12 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
Invert onto serving plate and remove foil.
Turn right side up.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and mix until well blended.
Spread over cooled crust. Arrange fruit on cream cheese.
Layer in a pinwheel design. Glaze with combined preserves and water.
Chill.
Cut into wedges.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter for graham cracker crumbs and mix butter with crumbs.
Pat crumbs into large shallow baking pan (about 9 x 18-inch).

title: thanksgiving dinner casserole
directions: Mix and divide Pepperidge Farm dressing, butter and chicken broth.
Put half in bottom of baking pan.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven. Brush top with melted margarine.
Continue baking 20 minutes more. Cool slightly before slicing.

title: dracula's worst nightmare
directions: Peel off outer layers of skin from whole garlic bulbs, leaving bulbs intact and cloves unpeeled.
Place bulbs in baking dish and drizzle with olive oil.
Fill baking dish with vermouth until garlic bulbs are half covered.
Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: spinach timbale
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a souffle dish and dust with 1/4 of bread crumbs.
Wash spinach and remove stems. Wilt in a dry frying pan.
Rinse under cold water; squeeze dry in a towel. Chop fine.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, water and cinnamon together.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, until all flour is well blended.
Halve dough and roll out on floured surface.
Cut with a cookie cutter. Bake in a 300° oven until lightly browned.
Immediately sprinkle a mixture of cinnamon and sugar over cookie.

title: orange honey glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir over low heat until well combined.

title: turkey chili(diet)
directions: *May substitute 1 pound lean ground beef.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups water and large tea bag to a boil; let simmer 10 minutes.
Take sugar, 2 cups water, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix together.
Let cool.
Add pineapple, orange and lime juices.
When ready to serve, mix equal parts water and juice.
Heat and then serve.
Great on a "cold" day.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until very tender.
In meantime, prepare ingredients.
Brown celery and garlic salt in butter.
Remove chicken from bones and tear into shreds (save broth).
Add chicken, onion, pepper, mushrooms, soup and pimentos to skillet. Cook the spaghetti in chicken broth until tender.
Place in large casserole dish a layer of spaghetti and layer of chicken sauce. Repeat layers.
Put grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 225°.

title: two-alarm chili
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain grease.
Add chili powder, garlic, tomato sauce and taco sauce; mix well.
Bring to boil; reduce flame.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in beans.
Cook until heated through.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice French bread in half lengthwise; core out bread, making 2 nice shells and set shells aside.
Tear cored out bread into small pieces and place in a large bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well and stuff back into the two shells.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, stuffing side up.
Bake about 45 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: mint tea
directions: Steep tea bags and mint in 6 cups boiling water. Add 1 1/2 pints ginger ale just before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine the ingredients in a large bowl in the following order: oil, sugar and eggs. Peel, core and chop fresh apples and add to the first mixture. Add nuts.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar and butter.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add milk and cook for 3 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm. Add vanilla and powdered sugar.

title: enchiladas
directions: Pour 1/2 can sauce into a 9 x 13 pan.
Place 1/8 of the browned beef into a tortilla; add cheese, then roll up the tortilla and place into pan.
Continue until all 8 are complete. Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas and sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: betty's baby shower punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding sherbet by the spoonful.
Float on top.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.

title: flat dumplings
directions: Combine all ingredients and add enough milk to mixture so you can roll out dough.
Cut any way you wish.
Drop in boiling broth.

title: chocolate polar bears
directions: Place milk, ice, Nesquik and ice cream in blender.
Cover. Blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Swirl in whipped cream. Serve immediately.

title: lemon icebox dessert
directions: Combine yolks, juice, rind, salt and sugar in double boiler. Cook until slightly thick.
Cool.
Whip cream; whip egg whites. Fold into lemon mixture and put in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex pan lined with graham cracker crust.
Freeze overnight.
Crumble crumbs on top too.
Serves 12.

title: herbed french bread chips
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Let foam.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix and knead 5 minutes.
Place in large greased bowl to rise one hour.
Knead on floured surface with herbs.
Divide into 3 loaves, brush with butter, stretch into long loaves and bake on a cookie sheet at 375° about 25 minutes.
Cool overnight.
Slice thin, brush with butter, put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Store open for crispness.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and corn.
Add sugar, milk, salt and butter.
Stir in the eggs.
Grease 1-quart casserole.
Pour in pudding.
Place in pan of hot water and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 loaf pans with Pam.
Mix flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Set aside.

title: moonballs(child-approved and healthy snack)
directions: Moosh first four ingredients together by hand.
Mold into 1-inch balls and roll in extra wheat germ.

title: m&m cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in vanilla and egg.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to sugar and egg mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in 1/4 cup M&M's (save some for decorating).
Drop rounded teaspoonful of cookie dough 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate tops with remaining candies.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour and fry until brown on all sides.
After frying, put chicken in baking dish.
Combine onion, vinegar, Worcestershire, catsup, mustard, salt and brown sugar in saucepan and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken and bake for 1 hour or more at 275°.
Cover baking dish before baking.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 6 hours.

title: jello shots
directions: You will need 1 package of little shot cups.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Beat together the oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder and mix well.
Spread 2/3 of batter in a greased sheet cake pan.
Cover this with cherry pie filling.
Dot remaining dough over the pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle with a powdered sugar glaze.
Other fruit pie fillings can be used.

title: banana foster
directions: Slice banana in 1/4 lengthwise and once across at center to make 8 pieces.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine and add enough water to make 2 cups.
After cake is cold, ice with whipped cream or Cool Whip and spread with fresh or frozen coconut.
Put in refrigerator.
Best made the night before or several hours before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cake mix with melted margarine and 1/2 can of milk.
Spread 1/2 batter in pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Melt caramels in 1/2 can milk while cake bakes.
Spread over baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Spread remaining batter on top and bake 15 minutes more. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in the peanut butter.
Mix in well the flour, baking powder and salt.
Spoon onto cookie sheets and cross tops with sugared fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: tangy punch
directions: Dissolve breakfast drink in water.
Add pineapple juice and lemonade concentrate.
Chill.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Season hamburger meat (salt, pepper, onions, bell pepper, etc.) and brown.
Mash biscuits flat and line sides and bottom of pie pan.
Put cheese on top of biscuit crust.
Drain hamburger meat and put on top of cheese in pie pan.
Bake at temperature shown on biscuit can until biscuits turn brown.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Add cinnamon to cake mix.
Beat salad dressing, cake mix, cinnamon, eggs and water at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in shredded carrots and nuts.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, which has been greased and lightly floured. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven or until tested done when touched lightly with fingers.
Cool completely before icing with your favorite icing.

title: cabbage
directions: Wash and quarter cabbage, then slice again to make eights. Precook until tender.
Drain cabbage; arrange in buttered casserole.
Spread mushroom soup.
Shred enough mild cheese to cover top.
Sprinkle bacon on top of cheese.
Cover top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
You can buy the bacon in a small can.
Use whole can.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry onion and sausage together.
Cook noodles.
Drain noodles. Drain sausage.
Mix together.
Add pizza sauce.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish, half of sausage and pizza sauce mix.
Top with 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 Cheddar cheese and 1/2 pepperoni.
Repeat with another layer.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and gravy
directions: Brown chicken on both sides.
Add remainder of ingredients. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and peel apples.
Pat out biscuits and place 4 or 5 slices per biscuit.
Sprinkle with cinnamon then fold over and press closed.
In a saucepan heat Sprite, 1 stick butter and sugar until sugar is melted.
Pour over biscuits and bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 13 x 9 pan.

title: spanish green beans
directions: Fry bacon in a large Dutch oven.
When almost cooked, add onion and bell pepper until browned (sauteed).
Add flour and stir, mixing ingredients thoroughly. Add tomatoes (cut them up some) and green beans.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: beef in sour cream
directions: Cut steak in cubes.
Put steak, flour, salt and pepper in bag and shake to coat.
Brown in pan with oil.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add to steak stirring over medium heat until steaming.
Cover and cook over low heat for 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with rice and English peas.

title: garden fresh pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls into a round pizza pan.
Brush with beaten egg and bake according to package directions.
Cool completely.

title: rancho potato salad
directions: In large bowl sprinkle potatoes with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and marinate in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 2 minutes on medium speed. Pour into well greased (not floured) Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers, onions and bell pepper.
Let stand 1 hour; drain.
Let sugar, vinegar and celery seed come to a boil; pour over cucumbers.
Let cool a little.
Put into containers and freeze.
Thaw before serving.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Prepare acini de pepe according to package directions; drain and set aside in very large bowl.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup of juice.
Pour juice into a small saucepan; add whipped egg and combine sugar and flour to remove lumps, then add to juice mixture.
Finally, add lemon juice.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until of pudding consistency.
Pour directly over drained noodles and chill several hours.
Just before serving, assemble by adding remaining ingredients.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: teatime tassies
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, margarine and flour.
Once this is mixed together, put in little cupcake pans like for pies.

title: beef 'n tater tot casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground meat and onion.
Spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Drain beans and save juice to add to soups.
Spread beans over meat and onion.
Combine juice with 2 cans of soup and heat to boiling point.
Pour over bean layer.
Cover with Tater Tots and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
In a 2-quart casserole, place carrots.
Pour celery soup over carrots and cover with the grated cheese.
Cover with onion rings and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain and cool.
Add eggs, onion, pickle relish, salt and pepper.
Can add mustard or mayonnaise.

title: russian beets
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Mix all remaining ingredients in the skillet with the onion. Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Saute onions, mushrooms and celery separately in butter.
Add soup, cheese, broccoli and cooked rice; pour into a baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: ahmads cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and water together.
Add cheese and sausage and mix with hands.
Roll in 1-inch balls on cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend well and chill.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, oil and poppy seed. Cut celery, cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces.
Mix well with other veggies.
Add oil mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease well two regular size bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Keeps good for several days.

title: annie's macadamia butter cookies
directions: *Macadamia nuts available at Sam's or Bulk Food Store; Macadamia butter can be found at the Honey Comb Store.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: In saucepan, heat together butter or margarine and 1/4 cup of the chocolate pieces over low heat just until melted.
Stir in oats until coated.
Press into the bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: good neighbor loaf
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
In medium bowl blend.
Mix thoroughly next ingredients in order given.
Add measured dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 1/2x4 1/2x3 pan.
Bake in preheated oven, 350 degrees for 1 hour. Cool on wire rack, wrap in wax paper.
Store in cake pan or bread box.

title: candied pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Line baking dish with slices of apple. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon; dot with butter.
Layer in pork chops, then repeat layering of apples, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp diablo
directions: First peel and devein the shrimp, then saute in olive oil until a pinkish red.
Add shallots, garlic, black pepper and parsley.

Cook this mixture over fast fire for 3 to 4 minutes. The recipe will then be a golden brown and have a delicate aroma. Add sherry, brown sauce, worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, dry mustard and catsup.
Cover skillet and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sever over a bed of long grain rice.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Mix well the butter, vanilla, salt and milk, enough to moisten, until smooth and creamy (I use my hands).
Divide in half and roll each piece 1/4-inch thick in an oblong shape in between two sheets of wax paper.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt Hershey candy and syrup in double boiler.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar; add whole eggs, one at a time.
Add chocolate mixture.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°, using greased tube pan.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Grind or chop fine the cranberries; add sugar and marshmallows. Mix and let set overnight.
Next day, add apples, grapes and nuts. Fold in cream just before serving.

title: lynn's teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix together and use to marinate steaks or chicken.
Best when marinated 4 hours minimum or overnight.
Grill or broil meat.
(Be ready with spray bottle of water to extinguish flare-ups.)

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix Ritz with Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Cut chicken into finger strips.
Dip in egg/milk mixture.
Roll in cracker crumb mixture.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn once.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 8-inch pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: star spangled special punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.
Add ice ring.
Serves 25.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Mix gelatin, water, sugar and strawberries.
Chill until syrupy.
Break up cake and pour gelatin mixture over cake, then stir in Cool Whip.
Turn out into glass bowl and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: taco spread
directions: Combine beans and taco seasoning.
Spread:
beans, sour cream, Pace hot sauce, avocado, cheese, olives and tomatoes.

title: quick rocky-road fudge
directions: Butter 8-inch square pan.
In large bowl, place chocolate chips, butter and shortening.
Microwave at High (100%) 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until chips are melted.
Add marshmallows and nuts; blend well.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Cover; refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, eggs and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients with milk.
Cream all mixtures together.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture into prepared cake pan.
Bake 1 hour and 14 minutes at 325°.

title: new orlean's style black pepper shrimp
directions: Place shrimp in a baking pan and completely cover with black pepper and then with sliced margarine.
Cover and bake in 400° oven until shrimp turns red.
Turn over once and cook the other side.
Serve hot.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Combine ingredients and beat well. Spread between layers and on top of cooled cake.

title: alice's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, cocoa, sugar and baking powder.
Add to sifted ingredients:
vegetable oil, milk and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes by mixer.
Dissolve baking soda in boiling water and add to batter.
Beat until mixed.

title: hawaiian dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Scoop out the middle of Hawaiian bread.
Place dip in center and serve at room temperature.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in a little salted water until tender; drain. In a saucepan, cook carrots and onions in butter until tender. Remove from heat; stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing cubes, the soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining butter.
Add remaining cubes; toss gently and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into balls and bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and green pepper; drain.
Add soup mix, chili powder, tomato sauce, tomato paste, olives and water. Simmer.

title: great biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in bowl.
Cut in Crisco with 2 knives.
Add milk and blend.
Roll dough 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with floured cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking pan in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 large biscuits.

title: herbed bubble loaf
directions: Thaw dough; allow to rise at room temperature 1 hour.
Knead both loaves into one ball.
Cut dough into 25 small pieces; shape into balls.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute onions.
Mix all ingredients.
Stuff cleaned mushrooms. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes covered.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix all vegetables with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight, refrigerated and covered.
Drain juices off. Tie mixed spices in flow through bag.
Add sugar and all spices to vinegar and simmer 20 minutes.
Add vegetables and simmer until hot and well seasoned.
Don't overcook.
Remove spice bag.
Pack hot chow-chow into hot Mason jars and seal immediately.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Roll one can of the crescent rolls between wax paper to fit the bottom	of a 12 x 18-inch pan.	Roll second can of the crescent rolls for the top of the filling.

title: for the crowd casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Saute onions.
Drain off fat.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Add vanilla, margarine and vinegar.
Over all pour 1 cup warm water and stir well but do not beat.
Bake in same pan in which mixed at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Stir together buttermilk, sugar, pecans, salt and margarine in a 4 or 5-quart dish.
Cook in microwave on High 12 minutes.
Stir at 4 minute intervals.
Stir in soda until foamy.
Cook on High 1 minute.
Beat mixture until tacky.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on sheet of foil.
Store in airtight container.

title: creamy caviar spread
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over wine in a small saucepan; let stand 1 minute.
Cook over low heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves. Combine sour cream and next 7 ingredients in container of electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Gradually add gelatin mixture. Pour mixture into a lightly greased 9-inch quiche dish.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
When ready to serve, invert spread onto serving platter.
Sprinkle egg along outer edge of top to form a 2-inch border.
Arrange a circle of green onions inside egg border.
Fill center with caviar.
Serve with water crackers.
Yields 4 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Place in small casserole dish.
Slice the butter and place on top of corn mixture.

title: turkey fillet with mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a skillet or pan gently melt 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Saute the mushrooms over medium heat until they are cooked.
You may add optional vinegar.
When mushrooms are done, put into a bowl leaving as much liquid as possible in the pan.
Dredge the turkey fillet in the flour to which you've added pepper to taste.
Shake fillet to loosen excess flour.
Melt the other tablespoon of butter or margarine in pan. Add the turkey fillet and saute over relatively high heat about 3 minutes until it is cooked through.
Pour the pan juices into a baking dish.
Add the fillet and then spoon the mushrooms on top. Cover with grated cheese of your choice and place in preheated oven.
Remove when the cheese has melted and serve.
To make more than one portion, simply multiply ingredients by the number of desired serving.

title: date orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs to butter and sugar.
Mix 3 1/2 cup flour with soda; add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in orange rind.
Coat dates and nuts with reserved
cup flour and fold into cake batter.
Bake in greased
and floured 10 inch tube or bundt pan at 275° for 2 hours.

title: toffee bar crunch pie
directions: Spread dessert topping on bottom of crust.
Pour milk into bowl; add pudding mix.
Whisk for 2 minutes; let stand 5 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip and chopped bars.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or until set.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before cutting.
Store in freezer.

title: beef enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in ground beef.
Put 1 layer of Fritos on bottom of pan and a layer of cheese.
Add ground beef, enchilada sauce and cream of mushroom soup.
Make 1 square casserole.
Top with a layer of cheese, then top with crushed Fritos.

title: chicken skillet casserole
directions: Saute onion, cut up chicken and broccoli until most of the margarine is absorbed.
Add soup with 1 can of milk and Velveeta cheese to taste (also cheese powder to taste). Add rice.
Use equal parts of milk and water to match amount of rice.
Cook until rice is tender.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat, rice, onion and bell pepper in oil.
Add tomato sauce and enough water to cover rice.
Add seasonings and simmer until rice is tender.
Add water as needed.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Microwave the chocolate chips on High for 2 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn halfway through cooking.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in milk, vanilla, powdered sugar, salt and marshmallows.
Microwave on High for 1 minute until marshmallows start to melt.
Add nuts; blend all ingredients well, making swirls in the candy.
Pour into a 12 x 8-inch dish which has been buttered.
Chill until firm.
Cut into desired size serving pieces.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds candy.

title: white steamed rice
directions: Mix and stir.
Cover for almost 20 minutes at low heat.
Turn fire off; wait 5 minutes and stir.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli/spinach until tender; drain.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Stir together apples, cranberries and sugar.
Place in slightly greased casserole dish.
Mix together pecans, oatmeal, flour, melted margarine and brown sugar.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake one hour at 325°.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and pepper. Cook for a minute longer.
Put all beans in crock-pot and stir to mix.
Put meat mixture on top, but do not stir.
Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt together butter and Velveeta cheese in microwave.
Stir to smooth.
Blend in 4 boxes confectioners sugar.
Add cocoa and vanilla.
Add lots of nuts.
Spread into pan.

title: orange sauce for gingerbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes. Drizzle over hot gingerbread.

title: choco-peanut oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 2-quart pan on burner; add butter and melt over low heat, stirring.
Turn off burner.
Place flour, oats, brown sugar, coconut and peanuts in bowl and mix.
Add butter to flour mixture and mix well.
Spoon into ungreased baking pan, scraping bowl.
Press mixture evenly into pan.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over warm cookie and spread evenly with spatula.
Let cool.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: spinach squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, beat eggs well; add flour, milk, salt and baking powder. Mix well.
Add cheese, spinach and onion.
Mix well.
Spoon into dish and level off.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool for 45 minutes.
Cut into bite size pieces. Freezes well.
Defrost, reheat at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: vinaigrette
directions: Place all ingredients except the garlic cloves in a 2-cup jar and seal well. Shake the jar until the sugar and salt are dissolved and ingredients well mixed. Add the garlic cloves and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: killer bread
directions: Preheat broiler.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and garlic in bowl. Arrange bread cut side up on large cookie sheet.
Butter bread. Broil until crisp and brown.
Spread cheese over top and sprinkle basil on top.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle pecans on bottom of dish.
Mix cake according to box directions.
Pour over pecans.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and butter.
Pour over cake mix. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate-blueberry dessert squares
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter, stirring well.
Press into bottom of ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until foamy. Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until blended.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Spread mixture evenly over crust; top with pie filling and sprinkle with 3/4 cup pecans.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In wok, slowly stir chicken broth into cornstarch.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Slowly pour in the well beaten egg.
Stir once gently.
Remove from heat.
Garnish with green onion.
Serves 4.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients. Stir well and chill.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In a medium saucepan, saute onion in oil until tender.
Add tomato puree and spices and mix well.
Cook on medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Set aside.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Stir in soured milk. Mix dry ingredients; stir in.
Stir in pecans, cherries and dates. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar.
Combine sugar, milk, flour and eggs. Stir together well.
Heat on top of stove.
Add your browned sugar and cook until sugar dissolves and mixture thickens.
Remove from stove and add vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli in a little butter until thawed.
Place in baking dish.
Heat soup and cheese until cheese melts.
Pour over broccoli.
Spread bread crumbs on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the hot water.
Add cherry juice.
Let cool until slightly thickened.
Soften the cheese with the 1/4 cup cream and add to the Jell-O mixture with the drained pineapple, cherries and nutmeats.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash potato and prick skin with fork. Bake 45 minutes or until soft.
Let cool, then cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out centers, leaving skin intact.
Place scooped out portions in a bowl and add remaining ingredients. Mash until smooth, then fill skins.
Heat for 20 minutes at 350°. Serves two.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on low heat for 2 hours.

title: venison stew
directions: Coat roast with flour and brown in hot skillet with cooking oil.
Remove meat from skillet and drain oil.
Brown onions and potatoes in skillet.
Add venison, remaining vegetables and soup mix in pressure cooker and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 40 minutes in pressure cooker or in Dutch oven for 2 hours.

title: bobbi's mints
directions: Mix food coloring with warm water and oil.
Mix in butter and sugar.
Knead and press into small candy molds.
Pop out and store in airtight bags.

title: fish stew
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large saute pan.
Saute the onion, garlic and green pepper over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, fennel, clam juice, wine, bay leaf, basil, thyme, orange peel, saffron, hot pepper flakes, black pepper and potatoes (or pasta).
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to a simmer, cover and let simmer for 15 minutes.
Add the clams, cover the pan and simmer until the clams open.
Discard any that don't open.
Add the squid, bass and shrimp.
Cover and simmer just until the fish are done, about 2 minutes.
Serve in deep bowls, garnished with parsley.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Peel, quarter and steam rutabagas (turnips).
Do not boil. When tender, mash.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Disjoint chicken wings or thighs, breasts and wings.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Dip in cornstarch, then into egg mixture.
Fry until golden brown.
Or place in baking pan or dish.
Pour Sweet and Sour Sauce over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (turning occasionally).

title: tijuana bean dip
directions: Microwave Directions:
In a 1 1/2-quart microwavable dish, combine beans, cheese, green onions and jalapeno peppers.
Cover with a piece of wax paper.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Stir in tomato, salsa and lemon juice.
Serve warm with Homemade Chips or Guiltless Gourmet baked low-fat tortilla chips.
Yields twelve 1/4-cup servings.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix salmon, cracker crumbs, eggs, salt and paprika.
Shape into cakes.
Saute them until brown in butter.

title: fiesta mexican pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook together until tender.
Add half of process cheese spread and chili powder. Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in tomato.

title: microwave crustless pizza pie
directions: Combine beef, onion, oats, egg, salt and pepper in mixing bowl.
Combine tomato sauce and oregano; mix half the sauce into the meat mixture.
Press in 9-inch glass pie plate.
Arrange pepper rings in center.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes; drain.
Spoon remaining tomato sauce over top.
Sprinkle with mushrooms and cheese.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes longer.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients. Crumble crackers. Make into cakes and fry.

title: stir-fry with rice
directions: Slice steak in thin strips.
Place in stir-fry pan with oil and brown slightly.
Add cornstarch and water and stir.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes with lid on.
Serve with herbed rice.

title: poor man's pie
