directions: Bring to boil peaches and sweetened to taste.
Pour in a cake pan.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Pour over fruit while fruit is boiling.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done. Cake will be on top when done.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Mix well.
Marinate 20 to 30 minutes.
Put the chicken on wooden skewer.
Cook on barbecue until done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook together sugar, milk, margarine and vinegar.
Cook to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Beat until thick.
Pour in greased pan and spread.

title: chicken in chipped beef
directions: Roll one strip of bacon around boned chicken.
Place in greased casserole.
Combine sour cream, mushroom soup and chipped beef.
Pour over chicken; cover.
Place in 300° oven and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: best ever chess pie
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar, corn meal, vinegar and evaporated milk to mixture.
Stir in melted butter and vanilla. Cover bottom of pie crust with chocolate chips.
Pour mixture over chips and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool before cutting.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat oil and eggs until foamy.
Stir in apples and sugar.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; stir in apple mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour batter into baking pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mix together the cheeses; set aside.
Mix together the soup, sour cream, onion, green chiles, olives and chicken pieces.
Layer corn tortillas and chicken mixture, then top with cheeses in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: saucy garden patch vegetables
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, milk, seasoned salt, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 onions in large bowl.
Spoon into 9 x 12-inch sprayed baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
Place in a 2-quart microsafe casserole.
Microwave on High power for 4 minutes.
Break up and stir.
Microwave on High power for 3 minutes, until pink color disappears.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Stir in onion, green pepper, garlic, tomatoes, water, oregano, basil, salt, pepper and spaghetti.
Stir to combine.
Push spaghetti down into liquid. Cover and microwave on High power for 8 minutes.
Stir and recover.
Microwave on High power for 9 to 10 minutes, until spaghetti is tender.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave, uncovered, on High power for 1 to 2 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serve hot from casserole.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder and stir into the egg mixture with eggnog.
Mix only until dry ingredients are moist.
Fold in nuts.
Grease and flour 1 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: seven layer dip
directions: In
a
glass or plastic container, layer above ingredients. First,
bean
dip;	2nd, avocado; 3rd, mayonnaise, sour cream
and taco
seasoning
mixed together; 4th, green onion; 5th,
sprinkle both cheeses; 6th, tomatoes (well drained) and 7th,
chopped olives.
Refrigerate
overnight.
Serve
with tortilla chips.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: roasted honey pepper pork
directions: Carefully score roast 1/2 inch deep completely around roast, without cutting string.
Combine all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon or brush 2/3 of honey mixture over pork to coat.

title: hamburger-n-spaghetti
directions: Cook in separate pot the spaghetti.
Drain and add to the sauce mixture.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: beef-up time . . . arizona style(servings:  8)
directions: Combine all ingredients except catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake together at 350° for 40 minutes per pound of meat. Cool.
Pull out bones, fat and gristle with your hands.
Shred meat.
Now add catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Reheat and "cook down" a little.
Serve on buns.
This is a wonderful make-ahead beef barbecue.
It doubles, triples and quadruples easily and freezes beautifully.

title: fruit casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan and pour fruit in.
Cut bread slices in 3 pieces and place on top of fruit.
Mix flour, sugar and eggs into batter.
Pour over bread strips and bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: cornell barbecue chicken(as in cornell university)
directions: Wash chicken (skin).
Mix sauce with a beater for about 2 minutes to emulsion consistency.
Heat sauce and chicken for about 20 minutes or so (just to boil).
Take chicken out and barbecue or broil for 30 minutes or until done, turning every 5 minutes.
Dunk chicken in sauce before each turn.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix and heat all in crock-pot.
Serve over taco chips.

title: german sugar cookies
directions: Mix
sugars,
oil
and	margarine.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add
flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix and chill at least 6 hours.
Roll in marble size balls.	Press flat with glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in airtight container and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 10 minutes before serving. Makes approximately 14 (6 ounce each) servings.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix half of Cool Whip, cream cheese, 2 tablespoons milk and sugar until fluffy.
Set aside.
Mix 3 1/2 cups milk and pudding. Layer in a bowl or clean clay flower pot, half the crushed cookies, cream cheese mixture, pudding mixture and remaining Cool Whip.
Top with remaining cookies.
Can decorate top with artificial flower and gummy worms.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix biscuit mix, raw sausage and cheese to form batter.
Fill pepper with cream cheese.
Cover with biscuit, sausage and cheese mixture.
Dip in batter; roll in bread crumbs and bake for 20 minutes in 325° to 350° oven.
Cook and freeze.
Heat and eat.

title: hamburger spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown onion, drain grease and brown meat.
Add cheese.
Add soup.
Mix spaghetti and top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch cream torte
directions: Mix flour, pecans, butter, and 2 tablespoons powdered sugar as pie crust and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
Beat together cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar and spread on cooled crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Beat pudding and milk.
Pour on second layer.
Refrigerate 2 hours until set.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.

title: dad's fudge cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, oil, water and cocoa.
Blend in mixing bowl the sugar, flour and salt.
Pour cocoa mixture into flour, sugar and salt mixture.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after adding each egg.
Add buttermilk into which soda has been added.
Add vanilla.
Batter will be rather sloppy. Bake in large jelly roll pan which has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
DO NOT OVERBAKE!
Soon as the cake comes out of the oven, frost.

title: keepsake brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Remove from heat. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Mix and sift together flour and salt; add gradually.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Steam zucchini and onion until transparent.
Spread crescent rolls on bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread mustard over crescent rolls.
Mix eggs, cheese and seasonings. Add steamed vegetables to egg mixture, then pour on crescent roll crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Make pudding per package directions.
Wait for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Put 1/2 of pudding mixture over them.
Put another layer of crackers on top, then rest of pudding on them.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Spread icing over top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: golden baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet with oil on top of stove.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking pan, add soups and water.
Bring mixture to a boil over burner on top of stove.
Add browned pork chops and bake for 40 minutes or until pork chops are tender in a 400° oven.

title: sopapillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Beat liquid ingredients and pour into dry ingredients.
Knead well.
Dough may be sticky.
Cover and let set for 20 minutes.
Roll thinly on floured board.
Cut into 3 to 4-inch squares or triangles and fry in deep hot oil. Drain and serve hot with honey.
Yields 16 pieces.

title: five-vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables in unsalted water following package directions.
Drain.
Stir in onions.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour dressing over mixed vegetables; cover and refrigerate at least 1/2 hour before serving, stirring often.

title: supreme white cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then vanilla and dry ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Roll into balls. Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: see's fudge
directions: Melt in large pan the milk and sugar, stirring constantly for 6 minutes.
In a large bowl put chocolate chips, marshmallows and butter.
Pour boiled mixture over chips.
Stir until smooth.
Add 2 cups of walnuts.
Put in well greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool 4 to 5 hours.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds of green peppers.
Cook in a saucepan in boiling salted water for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and place peppers into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: poor man's cake(raisin cake)
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Sift together the next 7 ingredients.
Mix baking soda in lukewarm water.
Add this to raisin mixture and stir into flour mixture by hand.
Pour into nongreased tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: anytime spinach bites
directions: Cook spinach and dried onion until spinach is totally defrosted; drain well.
Mix warm spinach and butter until butter is melted.
Add stuffing, cheese, Tabasco and sage.
Mix well. Stir in eggs.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
(May be frozen up to 4 months.)
Cook frozen bites on a greased baking sheet for 15 to 20 minutes in a 375° oven.
Bake thawed bites for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter (melted), sugars and peanut butter together.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Set in refrigerator for 5 minutes. Form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet, press flat with fork.
Bake at 350° until edges are light brown.

title: simple brownies
directions: Mix together melted butter, eggs and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.
If desired, you may top with chocolate icing.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars.
Beat in vanilla, water and eggs. Sift flour and other dry ingredients together and add sugar and egg mixture.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about three dozen 2 1/4-inch cookies.

title: hummus
directions: Blend all of the ingredients in a blender to desired consistency.
Mixture should be a paste, but neither dry nor soupy.
If necessary, add more liquid.

title: chocolate punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely. Mix puddings and milk until thick.
Crush candy bars.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream first four ingredients.
Add eggs, flour and flavoring. Bake at 270° about 2 hours.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Add apple, pineapple, orange and celery.
Mix together.
One cup chopped nuts is optional.
Refrigerate in covered container. Will keep 2 or 3 weeks.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 13-inch pan.
In frypan, cook the beef and onion until brown.
Drain. Stir in taco seasoning mix. Add water.
Cook until water evaporates, stirring occasionally. Spread in pan. Top with chillies.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture in pan. Bake 25 minutes. Top with beans (slightly cooked to make easier to spread).
Sprinkle grated cheese over beans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Drain beans, peas, and carrots.
Mix all ingredients and chill in a covered container overnight.
Keeps for several days. Serves 12.

title: skillet honeyed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini.
Cut off ends.
Cut into quarters lengthwise. In a medium skillet, combine honey, water and salad dressing mix. Arrange zucchini, cut side down, in honey mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes or until zucchini is fork-tender.
Add tomato wedges.
Cook several minutes longer, turning once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at at time, make a paste of cocoa and food color and add to cream mix.	Sift flour and salt together.
Alternate buttermilk and flour to cream mixture.
Mix soda and vinegar and add to batter.
Bake in 2- 9 inch or 3- 8 inch 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jalapeno fudge
directions: Shred cheeses and mix together.
Slightly beat eggs and pour onto cheeses; add peppers.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan for thick fudge or a 9 x 13-inch pan for thinner fudge.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.
It's wonderful!

title: garlic dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; serve with vegetables.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix corn, crumbs, salt and pepper.
Saute onion and parsley in butter.
Add to corn mixture with the beaten egg and apple.
Stir in the cream with a light touch.
Add poultry seasoning.
Stuff pockets in pork chops and brown on both sides in a heavy skillet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 1 cup stock or water in pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add more liquid, if necessary.

title: sloppy joes(makes approximately 4 servings))
directions: Brown hamburger; add onions, celery and green pepper.
Mix well.
Add vinegar, sugar and dry mustard.
Stir in catsup. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: In pan, saute mushrooms in oil for 5 to 6 minutes.
In 1/2 cup water, dissolve cornstarch and turmeric.
Hold.
Add minced garlic, salt and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Add slowly now 1/2 cup mixture of cornstarch and turmeric.
Stir as adding and boil about 2 minutes.

title: rolled baklava(strifto)
directions: Unfold package of filo and place on waxed paper.
Cover with more waxed paper and damp dish towel to prevent fila from drying and cracking.
Remove 3 fila at a time and place on flat surface. Brush each generously with melted butter, arranging one filo on top of the other.
Combine nuts, sugar, spices and vanilla. Sprinkle a few tablespoons of nut mixture evenly over two-thirds of the top buttered fila.
Starting with the filled edge, roll loosely in a jellyroll fashion to make a long roll.
Place in greased baking pan.
Continue filling pans with nut rolls, using 3 well buttered fila for each roll.
Cut each roll in 1 1/2-inch diagonal slices, leaving the rolls intact.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until golden. Cool.
Pour warm syrup over rolls in pan.
Let stand 1 hour. Makes about 60.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well. Dissolve cubes in boiling water and add to flour mixture along with the sugar and dry milk, if using.
Mix well to make a stiff dough.
Roll onto a floured surface and cut into shapes or strips.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand, uncovered, overnight to harden.

title: papa jacobs' barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except garlic.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use (or freeze).
Makes 6 pints.

title: the ultimate cheese ball
directions: Use food processor or blender to finely chop onion and pastrami.
Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans until well coated.
Refrigerate until an hour before serving.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix powdered sugar with 2 cups flour and soft butter together with a fork.
Press this coarse mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat together eggs; add 2 cups sugar plus lemon juice.
Add 1/4 cup flour plus baking powder.
Pour mixture over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Scramble hamburger and drain well.
Combine the hamburger, soups and Tater Tots and bake in 350° oven, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bacon broccoli salad
directions: I use 2 bunches broccoli with 1 cup mayonnaise mix.

title: orange slice candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together except confectioners sugar and place in a greased sheet cake pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 275°. Remove from oven and stir in box of confectioners sugar; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and let cool completely.

title: duffie's roast, deer, elk, moose, antelope, pork or beef
directions: Combine red wine, peanut
oil, Worcestershire sauce and lemon pepper.
Place roast in small pan and pour marinade over the roast.
Make sure it is
completely
covered.
Marinate in refrigerator for 16 hours.	Cook in
Dutch	oven
on low heat, about 300° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: strawberry-orange slush
directions: Combine first four ingredients in container of an electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Gradually add ice, processing until mixture reaches desired consistency.
Garnish each serving with a strawberry and orange wedge, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Yields 5 1/2 cups.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger, add to rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cold pack 3 hours or 90 minutes in a pressure cooker.
Makes 15 quarts.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown the ground beef in a 10-inch iron skillet.
Drain excess grease and add rest of ingredients in order given.
Heat and simmer until rice is of desired texture.
Stir frequently to reduce cooking time.

title: aunt margaret's cream cheese cake
directions: Mix French vanilla pudding mix with milk.
Whip on high 2 minutes.
Pour pudding mix over graham crackers in pan.
Layer with 2nd row of graham crackers.
Let set.
Continue to layer. Put chocolate icing on next, then Cool Whip.

title: bisquick taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown hamburger and onion in skillet. Drain.
Add taco seasoning and green chilies.
Spread in a quiche pan or large pie plate. Blend Bisquick milk and eggs in blender. Pour over meat mixture and bake about 25 minutes. Serve hot with lettuce, tomato and sour cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dutch slaw
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Stir in 3/4 cup sugar.
Boil remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage mixture.
Let stand overnight.

title: chocolate town house special cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add eggs; beat.
Add rest of ingredients, except cocoa and water.
Pour boiling water over cocoa and mix.
Add this to mixture, beating until well blended.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mom's tater salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done (longer if you want smashed potato salad).
Hard-boil the eggs.
Skin potatoes and dice.
Cool eggs and chop.
Mix ingredients.
Add about a cup of pickle juice.
Add enough mayo, thoroughly mixing, so that salad is moist throughout. I had a hard time with that sentence.
Just make sure that there's no dry clumps of potatoes.
Some like to put mustard in their potato salad.
Go ahead if you want to mess up a great recipe.
Liberally add pepper.
Salt to taste.
Best if left in icebox overnight to allow flavors to ferment.
Serve small army with enough left over for several potato salad sandwiches.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Stuff chicken breasts with ham slice and 1 slice Mozzarella cheese. Secure with toothpick; dip in beaten egg, then in cracker crumbs.
Melt 1 stick of butter in dish.
Place chicken in this and bake at 350° until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° about 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in oil until tender and drain.
Mix together soup, sour cream and carrots.
Add to zucchini and onion. Melt butter and combine with stuffing mix.
Put half of the stuffing mix on the bottom of a medium size baking dish.
Cover it with the zucchini mixture.
Top with remaining 1/2 of stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to boil and cook 4 to 5 minutes (start to time when mixture starts bubbling).
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute, until marshmallows blend and melt.
Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat until light sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add oats, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: In
medium size pan, crush vanilla wafers.
Melt butter and pour
over wafers to soften.
In mixing bowl mix together cream cheese,
lemon
juice
and milk until cheese is smooth. Pour over crushed vanilla wafers.
Chill until cheese is firm. Mix
jello according
to
package
and
pour over firm cheese mixture.
Chill again
until jello firms.	Top with Cool Whip and garnish with strawberries.

title: cottage cheese potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, green pepper, pimento, onion and pickle; toss lightly.
Chill.
Combine mayonnaise, seasonings and lemon juice.
Add to potato mixture.
Add cottage cheese; stir gently.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.
Recipe is from Hills and Pines Garden Club in Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and peanut butter together in a mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar and continue beating. Mix in egg, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir in flour and mix until thoroughly combined.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Mix in chocolate chips.

title: frosting
directions: Boil 4 1/2 tablespoons sugar and water 1 minute.
Beat egg, add powdered sugar and beat well.
Add syrup.
Add Crisco, vanilla and salt.
Beat until creamy.
If too thin, add more Crisco.
Add 1 tablespoon cocoa, if desired.

title: (mizeria) cukes and sour cream(polish style)
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice very thin rounds.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and set aside for 1 hour.
Drain off liquid. Season with salt and pepper if needed.
Add heavy sour cream, then add vinegar to taste.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the cream cheese in mixer and add sugar.
Slowly add eggs and beat well.
Stir in lemon juice, vanilla, flour and cornstarch.
Add margarine and fold in sour cream.
Pour into the spring-form pan and bake 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave in oven for 3 hours.
Take the spring-form pan from around the cake and refrigerate.
I wrap mine in Saran Wrap to keep it fresh.
Pour into a greased 9 x 4-inch spring-form pan.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Stir buttermilk and molasses into dry ingredients until well moistened.
Add raisins and nuts. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in 325° oven for 50 minutes. Freezes well.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Pour into pound cake pan or bundt pan.
Bake about 40 minutes in 350 degree oven or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: sherry seafood casserole
directions: Add mushrooms, seafood, sherry and cheese to soup.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over quick oats.
Stir and let stand 20 minutes or until completely cold.
Cream brown sugar, white sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and cold oats; mix well.
Add cinnamon, soda and salt.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy caramel
directions: Butter square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: diabetic jello salad
directions: Heat diet drink with gelatin.
Stir.
Add sweetener while still hot. Add cottage cheese and pineapple.
Stir until mixture sets.

title: poor man's raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins and water down to 1 cup juice; add soda and shortening to liquid while warm.
Add sugar and flour (enough to make a light batter, not a stiff one), baking powder and spices. Mix well and bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli and ham soup
directions: On 3-quart saucepan cook ham, onion and garlic in butter or margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in condensed chicken broth, fresh or frozen chopped broccoli, water, undrained tomatoes, uncooked macaroni and nutmeg.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until broccoli and macaroni are tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Sprinkle individual servings with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, brown sugar and margarine well; add egg and vanilla and mix well.
Add salt, baking soda, cream of tartar and flour, then add oatmeal, walnuts, coconut and Rice Krispies by hand.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: After mixing ingredients together, pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (A good do-ahead meal and can be frozen for up to 4 weeks.)

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage and tomato juice in a large bowl.
Wrap the meat mixture in the cabbage leaves as you would wrap a soft-shell taco. Pour tomato juice into a large pot. Add the wrapped stuffed cabbage to the pot and simmer for 1 hour on a gentle boil.

title: fresh pineapple "sundaes"
directions: Twist crown from pineapple.
Cut pineapple lengthwise into quarters.
Cut fruit from shell and core.
Cut pineapple into chunks.
Divide into 8 serving glasses.
Place milk and pudding mix into blender.
Process for 40 seconds or until well blended. Transfer to a large bowl.
Chill for 10 minutes.
Spoon over pineapple chunks.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Great for summertime afternoon snacks!

title: banana split cake
directions: Slice bananas and place on crust.
Drain pineapple and pour over the bananas.
Add Dream Whip as topping and garnish with chopped nuts and cherries.
Let set overnight.

title: frosty strawberry summer sensation
directions: Stir flour, sugar, walnuts and butter.
Sprinkle crumbly mixture onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Stir 3 times during baking to break up crumbs.
Whip egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add strawberries and lemon juice.
Beat at high speed about 10 minutes until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crumbs into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with strawberry mixture.
Top with rest of crumbs.
Cover and freeze 4 hours or longer until firm.
To serve, garnish each square with sliced fresh strawberries.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Mix together with remaining ingredients and 2 cups of the cheese.
Place in baking dish and top with remaining 1 cup of cheese.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Marinate at least 4 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms, remove stems and chop.
Cook pepperoni, onion, parsley flakes and chopped mushroom stems in butter about 3 minutes.
Mix in bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stuff mushroom caps with mix.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's no-bake cookies
directions: Mix oleo, cocoa, sugar and milk together in pan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off stove and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil with zucchini; mix well. Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: three piece pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add melted margarine and milk.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked brussels sprouts(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart casserole, stir all ingredients, except Brussels sprouts, until well blended.
Add Brussels sprouts; toss to mix well.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. No need to frost this cake.
Decorate with whipped topping and cherries.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix other ingredients except corn flakes.
Spread over potatoes and top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add grated carrots and mix well.
Add nuts and pour into a baking pan.
Bake for 35 minutes. Remove from oven and spread with icing.

title: basic cooked lentils
directions: Bring the ingredients to a boil; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add tomato paste, onions, vegetables or cheese for more flavor.
Serve plain or over rice.

title: happy holly glaze
directions: Bake ham according to package directions.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat slowly until smooth, beating with wire whisk or rotary beater.
Thirty minutes before ham is done, remove from oven.
Spoon 1/2 of glaze on ham surface.
Continue baking.
Serve ham with remaining glaze.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a bowl.
Pour into greased pie plates.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Place in slow cooker.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add pineapple with pie filling; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (glass dish).
Let set until congealed.

title: scalloped tomato casserole
directions: Layer half each of first 5 ingredients in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish; repeat layers. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Spread sour cream on top; sprinkle with croutons and drizzle with melted butter. Bake 10 more minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chops with pears
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika, pepper, garlic and poultry seasoning.
Shake each pork chop in this mixture until there are no moist spots on the meat.
Place chops in greased shallow baking pan.
Add as many pear halves as pork chops, placing the pears between the chops.
Add 1/2 teaspoon mayonnaise to each pear center.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Ovens may vary. Bake until chops are thoroughly cooked and brown.

title: dole golden layer cake
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, whipped topping and pudding mix; let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut cake lengthwise in thirds.
Drizzle with liqueur.
Spread 1/3 of the pudding mixture over bottom layer of cake.
Top with second layer.
Repeat layering, ending with pudding.
Chill 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with toasted, sliced almonds and garnish with pineapple slices.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Boil for 1 minute and beat.

title: creamy rice fudge
directions: Mix chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Cook uncovered on High heat for 2 minutes or until glossy and margarine is melted and chocolate chips retain their shape.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pie shell 5 to 6 minutes.
Sprinkle bacon (which was broiled to a crisp).
Put cheese slices to cover bottom of crust. Beat eggs, flour, salt, cayenne and nutmeg.
Add milk and butter. Stir well and pour into crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until custard is done and top is slightly brown.

title: cookies for santa
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix sugar, shortening, egg, honey and lemon extract. Stir in remaining ingredients. Roll dough 1/4 inch thick. Use cookie cutters to cut in desired shape. Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes. Cool and decorate.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: fettuccine verde
directions: Following package directions, cook fresh or dried noodles in a large kettle of boiling salted water until al dente, then drain.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Drain chicken breast.
Place in medium bowl and flake.
Add RoTel to chicken.
Mix in cheese.
Blend.
In large skillet over medium-low heat, place one tortilla with 1/2 cup chicken mix. Spread mix over tortilla and cover with a second tortilla.
Heat until cheese is melted, turning once.

title: cheesy egg casserole
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk, beating until smooth.
Beat in the cottage cheese and stir in the cubed cream cheese and cubed Monterey Jack cheese. Pour into a well greased and floured 2-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Mix all ingredients together except broccoli, melted butter and bread crumbs.
Put broccoli in baking dish; pour mixed ingredients over.
Mix butter (melted) and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of broccoli mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate snowflake cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add about 1/4 of dry mixture at a time to chocolate mixture, mixing after each addition.
Cover and chill dough at least 2 hours. Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in powdered sugar.
Place cookies 2-inches apart on aluminum foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Slide aluminum foil gently off baking sheet and let cool.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: pea salad(low-fat)
directions: Mix dressing, sour cream and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Garnish with 4 slices bacon, turkey bacon or 1 cup Bac*Os.
Enjoy.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease
tube pan and pour mixture in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Melt morsels in microwave.
Stir in nuts.
Drop on wax paper and put in freezer until set.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Mix in flour, vanilla, potato chips and nuts.
Drop tablespoons of dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press balls with glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Put in bowl that you can cover and then top with chopped nuts and coconut. This can be kept in the refrigerator up to a week. This also can be used for a dessert.

title: ann costa's chicken ratatouille
directions: Heat corn oil in large frying pan.
Add chicken and saute about 2 minutes on each side.
Add zucchini, eggplant, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes or until tender.
Add tomatoes with juice, stirring carefully.
Add garlic salt, flavor enhancer, basil, parsley and pepper.
Simmer about 5 minutes or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Serve chicken on large platter with mound of rice in center.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: the creamest dreamest cheese cake surprise
directions: Mix well, cream cheese and sour cream.
Add sugar slowly.
Mix in whipped cream slowly (mix until smooth).
Pour mixture in pie shell, spread evenly and top with cherry pie filling.
*Chill 2 hours before serving.* Your guests will love your cool no bake surprise!

title: dietetic apple crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make crumbs from bread toasted in the oven.
Mix crumbs with margarine, cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon allspice.
Mix apples with lemon juice, maple topping and the rest of allspice.
Spread in well greased shallow pan (8-inch round). Cover with crumb mixture and bake 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hostess peas
directions: Cook peas according to package directions; drain.
Saute onion in butter; blend in flour.
Gradually add half and half or milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Serves 6 to 8.
